{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["26-EZK-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"EZK"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["Ezekiel \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["The Book of Ezekiel \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["Ezekiel \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["Ezk \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt2","content":["The Book of \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Ezekiel \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"EZK 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 1:1"},"Now in the thirtieth year, in the fourth month, in the fifth of the month, as I was amongst the captives by the river\nChebar, the heavens were opened, and I saw visions of Allah.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The Hebrew word rendered “Allah” is “אֱלֹהִ֑ים” (Elohim)."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 1:2"},"In the fifth of the month, which was the fifth year of king Jehoiachin’s captivity,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 1:3"},"the LORD’s",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, “LORD” or “ALLAH” is the translation of Allah’s Proper\nName."]}],"caller":"+"}," word came to Ezekiel the priest, the son of Buzi, in the land of the Chaldeans by the river Chebar; and the LORD’s\nhand was there on him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 1:4"},"I looked, and behold,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Behold”, from “הִנֵּה”, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It\nis often used as an interjection."]}],"caller":"+"}," a stormy wind came out of the north: a great cloud, with flashing lightning, and a\nbrightness around it, and out of the middle of it as it were glowing metal, out of the middle of the fire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 1:5"},"Out of its centre came the likeness of four living creatures. This was their appearance: They had the likeness of a man.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 1:6"},"Everyone had four faces, and each one of them had four wings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 1:7"},"Their feet were straight feet. The sole of their feet was like the sole of a calf’s foot; and they sparkled like burnished\nbronze. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 1:8"},"They had the hands of a man under their wings on their four sides. The four of them had their faces and their wings like\nthis: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 1:9"},"Their wings were joined to one another. They didn’t turn when they went. Each one went straight forward.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 1:10"},"As for the likeness of their faces, they had the face of a man. The four of them had the face of a lion on the right\nside. The four of them had the face of an ox on the left side. The four of them also had the face of an eagle.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 1:11"},"Such were their faces. Their wings were spread out above. Two wings of each one touched another, and two covered their\nbodies. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 1:12"},"Each one went straight forward: where the spirit was to go, they went. They didn’t turn when they went.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 1:13"},"As for the likeness of the living creatures, their appearance was like burning coals of fire, like the appearance of\ntorches. The fire went up and down amongst the living creatures. The fire was bright, and lightning went out of the fire.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 1:14"},"The living creatures ran and returned as the appearance of a flash of lightning.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 1:15"},"Now as I saw the living creatures, behold, there was one wheel on the earth beside the living creatures, for each of the\nfour faces of it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 1:16"},"The appearance of the wheels and their work was like a beryl. The four of them had one likeness. Their appearance and\ntheir work was as it were a wheel within a wheel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 1:17"},"When they went, they went in their four directions. They didn’t turn when they went.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 1:18"},"As for their rims, they were high and dreadful; and the four of them had their rims full of eyes all around.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 1:19"},"When the living creatures went, the wheels went beside them. When the living creatures were lifted up from the earth, the\nwheels were lifted up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 1:20"},"Wherever the spirit was to go, they went. The spirit was to go there. The wheels were lifted up beside them; for the\nspirit of the living creature was in the wheels. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 1:21"},"When those went, these went. When those stood, these stood. When those were lifted up from the earth, the wheels were\nlifted up beside them; for the spirit of the living creature was in the wheels.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 1:22"},"Over the head of the living creature there was the likeness of an expanse, like an awesome crystal to look at, stretched\nout over their heads above. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 1:23"},"Under the expanse, their wings were straight, one towards the other. Each one had two which covered on this side, and\neach one had two which covered their bodies on that side. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 1:24"},"When they went, I heard the noise of their wings like the noise of great waters, like the voice of the Almighty, a noise\nof tumult like the noise of an army. When they stood, they let down their wings.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 1:25"},"There was a voice above the expanse that was over their heads. When they stood, they let down their wings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 1:26"},"Above the expanse that was over their heads was the likeness of a throne, as the appearance of a\nsapphire",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:26 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, lapis lazuli"]}],"caller":"+"}," stone. On the likeness of the throne was a likeness as the appearance of a man\non it above. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 1:27"},"I saw as it were glowing metal, as the appearance of fire within it all around, from the appearance of his waist and\nupward; and from the appearance of his waist and downward I saw as it were the appearance of fire, and there was brightness\naround him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 1:28"},"As the appearance of the rainbow that is in the cloud in the day of rain, so was the appearance of the brightness all\naround. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["This was the appearance of the likeness of the LORD’s glory. When I saw it, I fell on my face, and I heard a voice of one\nthat spoke. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"EZK 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 2:1"},"He said to me, “Son of man, stand on your feet, and I will speak with you.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 2:2"},"The Spirit entered into me when he spoke to me, and set me on my feet; and I heard him who spoke to me.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 2:3"},"He said to me, “Son of man, I send you to the children of Israel, to a nation of rebels who have rebelled against me. They\nand their fathers have transgressed against me even to this very day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 2:4"},"The children are impudent and stiff-hearted. I am sending you to them, and you shall tell them, ‘This is what the\nLord",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word translated “Lord” is “Adonai.”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ALLAH says.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 2:5"},"They, whether they will hear, or whether they will refuse, for they are a rebellious house, yet they will know that there\nhas been a prophet amongst them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 2:6"},"You, son of man, don’t be afraid of them, neither be afraid of their words, though briers and thorns are with you, and you\ndwell amongst scorpions. Don’t be afraid of their words, nor be dismayed at their looks, though they are a rebellious house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 2:7"},"You shall speak my words to them, whether they will hear, or whether they will refuse; for they are most rebellious.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 2:8"},"But you, son of man, hear what I tell you. Don’t be rebellious like that rebellious house. Open your mouth, and eat that\nwhich I give you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 2:9"},"When I looked, behold, a hand was stretched out to me; and, behold, a scroll of a book was in it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 2:10"},"He spread it before me. It was written within and without; and lamentations, mourning, and woe were written in it.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"EZK 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 3:1"},"He said to me, “Son of man, eat what you find. Eat this scroll, and go, speak to the house of Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 3:2"},"So I opened my mouth, and he caused me to eat the scroll. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 3:3"},"He said to me, “Son of man, cause your belly to eat, and fill your bowels with this scroll that I give you.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then I ate it; and it was as sweet as honey in my mouth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 3:4"},"He said to me, “Son of man, go to the house of Israel, and speak my words to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 3:5"},"For you are not sent to a people of a strange speech and of a hard language, but to the house of Israel;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 3:6"},"not to many peoples of a strange speech and of a hard language, whose words you can’t understand. Surely, if I sent you to\nthem, they would listen to you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 3:7"},"But the house of Israel will not listen to you, for they will not listen to me; for all the house of Israel are\nobstinate",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["3:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally, have a hard forehead"]}],"caller":"+"}," and hard-hearted.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 3:8"},"Behold, I have made your face hard against their faces, and your forehead hard against their foreheads.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 3:9"},"I have made your forehead as a diamond, harder than flint. Don’t be afraid of them, neither be dismayed at their looks,\nthough they are a rebellious house.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 3:10"},"Moreover he said to me, “Son of man, receive in your heart and hear with your ears all my words that I speak to you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 3:11"},"Go to them of the captivity, to the children of your people, and speak to them, and tell them, ‘This is what the Lord\nALLAH says,’ whether they will hear, or whether they will refuse.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 3:12"},"Then the Spirit lifted me up, and I heard behind me the voice of a great rushing, saying, “Blessed be the LORD’s glory\nfrom his place.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 3:13"},"I heard the noise of the wings of the living creatures as they touched one another, and the noise of the wheels beside\nthem, even the noise of a great rushing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 3:14"},"So the Spirit lifted me up, and took me away; and I went in bitterness, in the heat of my spirit; and the LORD’s hand was\nstrong on me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 3:15"},"Then I came to them of the captivity at Tel Aviv, that lived by the river Chebar, and to where they lived; and I sat\nthere overwhelmed amongst them seven days. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 3:16"},"At the end of seven days, the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 3:17"},"“Son of man, I have made you a watchman to the house of Israel. Therefore hear the word from my mouth, and warn them from\nme. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 3:18"},"When I tell the wicked, ‘You will surely die;’ and you give him no warning, nor speak to warn the wicked from his wicked\nway, to save his life; that wicked man will die in his iniquity; but I will require his blood at your hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 3:19"},"Yet if you warn the wicked, and he doesn’t turn from his wickedness, nor from his wicked way, he will die in his\niniquity; but you have delivered your soul.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 3:20"},"“Again, when a righteous man turns from his righteousness, and commits iniquity, and I lay a stumbling block before him,\nhe will die. Because you have not given him warning, he will die in his sin, and his righteous deeds which he has done will not\nbe remembered; but I will require his blood at your hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 3:21"},"Nevertheless if you warn the righteous man, that the righteous not sin, and he does not sin, he will surely live, because\nhe took warning; and you have delivered your soul.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 3:22"},"the LORD’s hand was there on me; and he said to me, “Arise, go out into the plain, and I will talk with you there.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 3:23"},"Then I arose, and went out into the plain, and behold, the LORD’s glory stood there, like the glory which I saw by the\nriver Chebar. Then I fell on my face. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 3:24"},"Then the Spirit entered into me, and set me on my feet. He spoke with me, and said to me, “Go, shut yourself inside your\nhouse. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 3:25"},"But you, son of man, behold, they will put ropes on you, and will bind you with them, and you will not go out amongst\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 3:26"},"I will make your tongue stick to the roof of your mouth, that you will be mute, and will not be able to correct them; for\nthey are a rebellious house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 3:27"},"But when I speak with you, I will open your mouth, and you shall tell them, ‘This is what the Lord ALLAH says.’ He who\nhears, let him hear; and he who refuses, let him refuse; for they are a rebellious house.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"4","sid":"EZK 4"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 4:1"},"“You also, son of man, take a tile, and lay it before yourself, and portray on it a city, even Jerusalem.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 4:2"},"Lay siege against it, build forts against it, and cast up a mound against it. Also set camps against it and plant\nbattering rams against it all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 4:3"},"Take for yourself an iron pan, and set it for a wall of iron between you and the city. Then set your face towards it. It\nwill be besieged, and you shall lay siege against it. This shall be a sign to the house of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 4:4"},"“Moreover lie on your left side, and lay the iniquity of the house of Israel on it. According to the number of the days\nthat you shall lie on it, you shall bear their iniquity. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 4:5"},"For I have appointed the years of their iniquity to be to you a number of days, even three hundred and ninety days. So you\nshall bear the iniquity of the house of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 4:6"},"“Again, when you have accomplished these, you shall lie on your right side, and shall bear the iniquity of the house of\nJudah. I have appointed forty days, each day for a year, to you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 4:7"},"You shall set your face towards the siege of Jerusalem, with your arm uncovered; and you shall prophesy against it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 4:8"},"Behold, I put ropes on you, and you shall not turn yourself from one side to the other, until you have accomplished the\ndays of your siege. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 4:9"},"“Take for yourself also wheat, barley, beans, lentils, millet, and spelt, and put them in one vessel. Make bread of it.\nAccording to the number of the days that you will lie on your side, even three hundred and ninety days, you shall eat of it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 4:10"},"Your food which you shall eat shall be by weight, twenty shekels",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," a day. From time to time you shall eat it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 4:11"},"You shall drink water by measure, the sixth part of a hin.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["4:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A hin is about 6.5 litres or 1.7 gallons."]}],"caller":"+"}," From time to time you shall drink.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 4:12"},"You shall eat it as barley cakes, and you shall bake it in their sight with dung that comes out of man.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 4:13"},"The LORD said, “Even thus will the children of Israel eat their bread unclean, amongst the nations where I will drive\nthem.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 4:14"},"Then I said, “Ah Lord ALLAH! Behold, my soul has not been polluted; for from my youth up even until now I have not eaten\nof that which dies of itself, or is torn of animals. No abominable meat has come into my mouth!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 4:15"},"Then he said to me, “Behold, I have given you cow’s dung for man’s dung, and you shall prepare your bread on it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 4:16"},"Moreover he said to me, “Son of man, behold, I will break the staff of bread in Jerusalem. They will eat bread by weight,\nand with fearfulness. They will drink water by measure, and in dismay;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 4:17"},"that they may lack bread and water, be dismayed one with another, and pine away in their iniquity.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"5","sid":"EZK 5"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 5:1"},"“You, son of man, take a sharp sword. You shall take it as a barber’s razor to yourself, and shall cause it to pass over\nyour head and over your beard. Then take balances to weigh and divide the hair.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 5:2"},"A third part you shall burn in the fire in the middle of the city, when the days of the siege are fulfilled. You shall\ntake a third part, and strike with the sword around it. A third part you shall scatter to the wind, and I will draw out a sword\nafter them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 5:3"},"You shall take of it a few in number, and bind them in the folds of your robe.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 5:4"},"Of these again you shall take, and cast them into the middle of the fire, and burn them in the fire. From it a fire will\ncome out into all the house of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 5:5"},"“The Lord ALLAH says: ‘This is Jerusalem. I have set her in the middle of the nations, and countries are around her.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 5:6"},"She has rebelled against my ordinances in doing wickedness more than the nations, and against my statutes more than the\ncountries that are around her; for they have rejected my ordinances, and as for my statutes, they have not walked in them.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 5:7"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Because you are more turbulent than the nations that are around you, and have not walked\nin my statutes, neither have kept my ordinances, neither have followed the ordinances of the nations that are around you;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 5:8"},"therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I, even I, am against you; and I will execute judgements amongst you in the sight\nof the nations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 5:9"},"I will do in you that which I have not done, and which I will not do anything like it any more, because of all your\nabominations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 5:10"},"Therefore the fathers will eat the sons within you, and the sons will eat their fathers. I will execute judgements on\nyou; and I will scatter the whole remnant of you to all the winds.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 5:11"},"Therefore as I live,’ says the Lord ALLAH, ‘surely, because you have defiled my sanctuary with all your detestable\nthings, and with all your abominations, therefore I will also diminish you. My eye won’t spare, and I will have no pity.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 5:12"},"A third part of you will die with the pestilence, and they will be consumed with famine within you. A third part will\nfall by the sword around you. A third part I will scatter to all the winds, and will draw out a sword after them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 5:13"},"“‘Thus my anger will be accomplished, and I will cause my wrath towards them to rest, and I will be comforted. They will\nknow that I, the LORD, have spoken in my zeal, when I have accomplished my wrath on them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 5:14"},"“‘Moreover I will make you a desolation and a reproach amongst the nations that are around you, in the sight of all that\npass by. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 5:15"},"So it will be a reproach and a taunt, an instruction and an astonishment, to the nations that are around you, when I\nexecute judgements on you in anger and in wrath, and in wrathful rebukes—I, the LORD, have spoken it—\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 5:16"},"when I send on them the evil arrows of famine that are for destruction, which I will send to destroy you. I will increase\nthe famine on you, and will break your staff of bread. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 5:17"},"I will send on you famine and evil animals, and they will bereave you. Pestilence and blood will pass through you. I will\nbring the sword on you. I, the LORD, have spoken it.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"6","sid":"EZK 6"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 6:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 6:2"},"“Son of man, set your face towards the mountains of Israel, and prophesy to them,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 6:3"},"and say, ‘You mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord ALLAH! The Lord ALLAH says to the mountains and to the hills,\nto the watercourses and to the valleys: “Behold, I, even I, will bring a sword on you, and I will destroy your high places.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 6:4"},"Your altars will become desolate, and your incense altars will be broken. I will cast down your slain men before your\nidols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 6:5"},"I will lay the dead bodies of the children of Israel before their idols. I will scatter your bones around your altars.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 6:6"},"In all your dwelling places, the cities will be laid waste and the high places will be desolate; that your altars may be\nlaid waste and made desolate, and your idols may be broken and cease, and your incense altars may be cut down, and your works\nmay be abolished. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 6:7"},"The slain will fall amongst you, and you will know that I am the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 6:8"},"“‘“Yet I will leave a remnant, in that you will have some that escape the sword amongst the nations, when you are\nscattered through the countries. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 6:9"},"Those of you that escape will remember me amongst the nations where they are carried captive, how I have been broken with\ntheir lewd heart, which has departed from me, and with their eyes, which play the prostitute after their idols. Then they will\nloathe themselves in their own sight for the evils which they have committed in all their abominations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 6:10"},"They will know that I am the LORD. I have not said in vain that I would do this evil to them.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 6:11"},"“The Lord ALLAH says: ‘Strike with your hand, and stamp with your foot, and say, “Alas!” Because of all the evil\nabominations of the house of Israel; for they will fall by the sword, by the famine, and by the pestilence.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 6:12"},"He who is far off will die of the pestilence. He who is near will fall by the sword. He who remains and is besieged will\ndie by the famine. Thus I will accomplish my wrath on them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 6:13"},"You will know that I am the LORD, when their slain men are amongst their idols around their altars, on every high hill,\non all the tops of the mountains, under every green tree, and under every thick oak, the places where they offered pleasant\naroma to all their idols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 6:14"},"I will stretch out my hand on them, and make the land desolate and waste, from the wilderness towards Diblah, throughout\nall their habitations. Then they will know that I am the LORD.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"7","sid":"EZK 7"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 7:1"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 7:2"},"“You, son of man, the Lord ALLAH says to the land of Israel, ‘An end! The end has come on the four corners of the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 7:3"},"Now is the end on you, and I will send my anger on you, and will judge you according to your ways. I will bring on you all\nyour abominations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 7:4"},"My eye will not spare you, neither will I have pity; but I will bring your ways on you, and your abominations will be\namongst you. Then you will know that I am the LORD.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 7:5"},"“The Lord ALLAH says: ‘An evil! A unique evil! Behold, it comes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 7:6"},"An end has come. The end has come! It awakes against you. Behold, it comes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 7:7"},"Your doom has come to you, inhabitant of the land! The time has come! The day is near, a day of tumult, and not of joyful\nshouting, on the mountains. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 7:8"},"Now I will shortly pour out my wrath on you, and accomplish my anger against you, and will judge you according to your\nways. I will bring on you all your abominations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 7:9"},"My eye won’t spare, neither will I have pity. I will punish you according to your ways. Your abominations will be amongst\nyou. Then you will know that I, the LORD, strike. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 7:10"},"“‘Behold, the day! Behold, it comes! Your doom has gone out. The rod has blossomed. Pride has budded.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 7:11"},"Violence has risen up into a rod of wickedness. None of them will remain, nor of their multitude, nor of their wealth.\nThere will be nothing of value amongst them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 7:12"},"The time has come! The day draws near. Don’t let the buyer rejoice, nor the seller mourn; for wrath is on all its\nmultitude. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 7:13"},"For the seller won’t return to that which is sold, although they are still alive; for the vision concerns the whole\nmultitude of it. None will return. None will strengthen himself in the iniquity of his life.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 7:14"},"They have blown the trumpet, and have made all ready; but no one goes to the battle; for my wrath is on all its\nmultitude. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 7:15"},"“‘The sword is outside, and the pestilence and the famine within. He who is in the field will die by the sword. He who is\nin the city will be devoured by famine and pestilence. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 7:16"},"But those of those who escape, they will escape and will be on the mountains like doves of the valleys, all of them\nmoaning, everyone in his iniquity. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 7:17"},"All hands will be feeble, and all knees will be weak as water.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 7:18"},"They will also clothe themselves with sackcloth, and horror will cover them. Shame will be on all faces, and baldness on\nall their heads. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 7:19"},"They will cast their silver in the streets, and their gold will be as an unclean thing. Their silver and their gold won’t\nbe able to deliver them in the day of the LORD’s wrath. They won’t satisfy their souls or fill their bellies; because it has\nbeen the stumbling block of their iniquity. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 7:20"},"As for the beauty of his ornament, he set it in majesty; but they made the images of their abominations and their\ndetestable things therein. Therefore I have made it to them as an unclean thing.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 7:21"},"I will give it into the hands of the strangers for a prey, and to the wicked of the earth for a plunder; and they will\nprofane it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 7:22"},"I will also turn my face from them, and they will profane my secret place. Robbers will enter into it, and profane it.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 7:23"},"“‘Make chains; for the land is full of bloody crimes, and the city is full of violence.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 7:24"},"Therefore I will bring the worst of the nations, and they will possess their houses. I will also make the pride of the\nstrong to cease. Their holy places will be profaned. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 7:25"},"Destruction comes! They will seek peace, and there will be none.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 7:26"},"Mischief will come on mischief, and rumour will be on rumour. They will seek a vision of the prophet; but the law will\nperish from the priest, and counsel from the elders. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 7:27"},"The king will mourn, and the prince will be clothed with desolation. The hands of the people of the land will be\ntroubled. I will do to them after their way, and according to their own judgements I will judge them. Then they will know that\nI am the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"8","sid":"EZK 8"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 8:1"},"In the sixth year, in the sixth month, in the fifth day of the month, as I sat in my house, and the elders of Judah sat\nbefore me, the Lord ALLAH’s hand fell on me there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 8:2"},"Then I saw, and behold, a likeness as the appearance of fire; from the appearance of his waist and downward, fire; and\nfrom his waist and upward, as the appearance of brightness, as it were glowing metal.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 8:3"},"He stretched out the form of a hand, and took me by a lock of my head; and the Spirit lifted me up between earth and the\nsky, and brought me in the visions of Allah to Jerusalem, to the door of the gate of the inner court that looks towards the\nnorth; where there was the seat of the image of jealousy, which provokes to jealousy.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 8:4"},"Behold, the glory of Allah of Israel was there, according to the appearance that I saw in the plain.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 8:5"},"Then he said to me, “Son of man, lift up your eyes now the way towards the north.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So I lifted up my eyes the way towards the north, and saw, northward of the gate of the altar this image of jealousy in the\nentry. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 8:6"},"He said to me, “Son of man, do you see what they do? Even the great abominations that the house of Israel commit here,\nthat I should go far off from my sanctuary? But you will again see yet other great abominations.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 8:7"},"He brought me to the door of the court; and when I looked, behold, a hole in the wall.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 8:8"},"Then he said to me, “Son of man, dig now in the wall.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["When I had dug in the wall, I saw a door. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 8:9"},"He said to me, “Go in, and see the wicked abominations that they do here.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 8:10"},"So I went in and looked, and saw every form of creeping things, abominable animals, and all the idols of the house of\nIsrael, portrayed around on the wall. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 8:11"},"Seventy men of the elders of the house of Israel stood before them. In the middle of them Jaazaniah the son of Shaphan\nstood, every man with his censer in his hand; and the smell of the cloud of incense went up.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 8:12"},"Then he said to me, “Son of man, have you seen what the elders of the house of Israel do in the dark, every man in his\nrooms of imagery? For they say, ‘The LORD doesn’t see us. The LORD has forsaken the land.’”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 8:13"},"He said also to me, “You will again see more of the great abominations which they do.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 8:14"},"Then he brought me to the door of the gate of the LORD’s house which was towards the north; and I saw the women sit there\nweeping for Tammuz. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 8:15"},"Then he said to me, “Have you seen this, son of man? You will again see yet greater abominations than these.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 8:16"},"He brought me into the inner court of the LORD’s house; and I saw at the door of the LORD’s temple, between the porch and\nthe altar, there were about twenty-five men, with their backs towards the LORD’s temple, and their faces towards the east. They\nwere worshipping the sun towards the east. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 8:17"},"Then he said to me, “Have you seen this, son of man? Is it a light thing to the house of Judah that they commit the\nabominations which they commit here? For they have filled the land with violence, and have turned again to provoke me to anger.\nBehold, they put the branch to their nose. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 8:18"},"Therefore I will also deal in wrath. My eye won’t spare, neither will I have pity. Though they cry in my ears with a loud\nvoice, yet I will not hear them.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"9","sid":"EZK 9"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 9:1"},"Then he cried in my ears with a loud voice, saying, “Cause those who are in charge of the city to draw near, each man with\nhis destroying weapon in his hand.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 9:2"},"Behold, six men came from the way of the upper gate, which lies towards the north, every man with his slaughter weapon in\nhis hand. One man in the middle of them was clothed in linen, with a writer’s inkhorn by his side. They went in, and stood\nbeside the bronze altar. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 9:3"},"The glory of Allah of Israel went up from the cherub, whereupon it was, to the threshold of the house; and he called to\nthe man clothed in linen, who had the writer’s inkhorn by his side.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 9:4"},"The LORD said to him, “Go through the middle of the city, through the middle of Jerusalem, and set a mark on the foreheads\nof the men that sigh and that cry over all the abominations that are done within it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 9:5"},"To the others he said in my hearing, “Go through the city after him, and strike. Don’t let your eye spare, neither have\npity. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 9:6"},"Kill utterly the old man, the young man, the virgin, little children and women; but don’t come near any man on whom is the\nmark. Begin at my sanctuary.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then they began at the old men who were before the house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 9:7"},"He said to them, “Defile the house, and fill the courts with the slain. Go out!”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["They went out, and struck in the city. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 9:8"},"While they were killing, and I was left, I fell on my face, and cried, and said, “Ah Lord ALLAH! Will you destroy all the\nresidue of Israel in your pouring out of your wrath on Jerusalem?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 9:9"},"Then he said to me, “The iniquity of the house of Israel and Judah is exceedingly great, and the land is full of blood,\nand the city full of perversion; for they say, ‘The LORD has forsaken the land, and the LORD doesn’t see.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 9:10"},"As for me also, my eye won’t spare, neither will I have pity, but I will bring their way on their head.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 9:11"},"Behold, the man clothed in linen, who had the inkhorn by his side, reported the matter, saying, “I have done as you have\ncommanded me.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"10","sid":"EZK 10"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 10:1"},"Then I looked, and see, in the expanse that was over the head of the cherubim there appeared above them as it were a\nsapphire",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["10:1 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, lapis lazuli "]}],"caller":"+"}," stone, as the appearance of the likeness of a throne.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 10:2"},"He spoke to the man clothed in linen, and said, “Go in between the whirling wheels, even under the cherub, and fill both\nyour hands with coals of fire from between the cherubim, and scatter them over the city.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["He went in as I watched. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 10:3"},"Now the cherubim stood on the right side of the house, when the man went in; and the cloud filled the inner court.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 10:4"},"The LORD’s glory mounted up from the cherub, and stood over the threshold of the house; and the house was filled with the\ncloud, and the court was full of the brightness of the LORD’s glory.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 10:5"},"The sound of the wings of the cherubim was heard even to the outer court, as the voice of Allah Ta’ala when he speaks.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 10:6"},"It came to pass, when he commanded the man clothed in linen, saying, “Take fire from between the whirling wheels, from\nbetween the cherubim,” that he went in, and stood beside a wheel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 10:7"},"The cherub stretched out his hand from between the cherubim to the fire that was between the cherubim, and took some of\nit, and put it into the hands of him who was clothed in linen, who took it and went out.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 10:8"},"The form of a man’s hand appeared here in the cherubim under their wings.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 10:9"},"I looked, and behold, there were four wheels beside the cherubim, one wheel beside one cherub, and another wheel beside\nanother cherub. The appearance of the wheels was like a beryl stone.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 10:10"},"As for their appearance, the four of them had one likeness, like a wheel within a wheel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 10:11"},"When they went, they went in their four directions. They didn’t turn as they went, but to the place where the head looked\nthey followed it. They didn’t turn as they went. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 10:12"},"Their whole body, including their backs, their hands, their wings, and the wheels, were full of eyes all around, even the\nwheels that the four of them had. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 10:13"},"As for the wheels, they were called in my hearing, “the whirling wheels”.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 10:14"},"Every one them had four faces. The first face was the face of the cherub. The second face was the face of a man. The\nthird face was the face of a lion. The fourth was the face of an eagle.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 10:15"},"The cherubim mounted up. This is the living creature that I saw by the river Chebar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 10:16"},"When the cherubim went, the wheels went beside them; and when the cherubim lifted up their wings to mount up from the\nearth, the wheels also didn’t turn from beside them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 10:17"},"When they stood, these stood. When they mounted up, these mounted up with them; for the spirit of the living creature was\nin them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 10:18"},"The LORD’s glory went out from over the threshold of the house, and stood over the cherubim.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 10:19"},"The cherubim lifted up their wings, and mounted up from the earth in my sight when they went out, with the wheels beside\nthem. Then they stood at the door of the east gate of the LORD’s house; and the glory of Allah of Israel was over them above.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 10:20"},"This is the living creature that I saw under Allah of Israel by the river Chebar; and I knew that they were cherubim.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 10:21"},"Every one had four faces, and every one four wings. The likeness of the hands of a man was under their wings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 10:22"},"As for the likeness of their faces, they were the faces which I saw by the river Chebar, their appearances and\nthemselves. They each went straight forward. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"11","sid":"EZK 11"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 11:1"},"Moreover the Spirit lifted me up, and brought me to the east gate of the LORD’s house, which looks eastward. Behold,\ntwenty-five men were at the door of the gate; and I saw amongst them Jaazaniah the son of Azzur, and Pelatiah the son of\nBenaiah, princes of the people. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 11:2"},"He said to me, “Son of man, these are the men who devise iniquity, and who give wicked counsel in this city;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 11:3"},"who say, ‘The time is not near to build houses. This is the cauldron, and we are the meat.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 11:4"},"Therefore prophesy against them. Prophesy, son of man.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 11:5"},"The LORD’s Spirit fell on me, and he said to me, “Speak, ‘The LORD says: “Thus you have said, house of Israel; for I know\nthe things that come into your mind. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 11:6"},"You have multiplied your slain in this city, and you have filled its streets with the slain.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 11:7"},"“‘Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “Your slain whom you have laid in the middle of it, they are the meat, and this is the\ncauldron; but you will be brought out of the middle of it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 11:8"},"You have feared the sword; and I will bring the sword on you,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 11:9"},"“I will bring you out of the middle of it, and deliver you into the hands of strangers, and will execute judgements\namongst you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 11:10"},"You will fall by the sword. I will judge you in the border of Israel. Then you will know that I am the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 11:11"},"This will not be your cauldron, neither will you be the meat in the middle of it. I will judge you in the border of\nIsrael. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 11:12"},"You will know that I am the LORD, for you have not walked in my statutes, You have not executed my ordinances, but have\ndone after the ordinances of the nations that are around you.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 11:13"},"When I prophesied, Pelatiah the son of Benaiah died. Then I fell down on my face, and cried with a loud voice, and said,\n“Ah Lord ALLAH! Will you make a full end of the remnant of Israel?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 11:14"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 11:15"},"“Son of man, your brothers, even your brothers, the men of your relatives, and all the house of Israel, all of them, are\nthey to whom the inhabitants of Jerusalem have said, ‘Go far away from the LORD. This land has been given to us for a\npossession.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 11:16"},"“Therefore say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Whereas I have removed them far off amongst the nations, and whereas I have\nscattered them amongst the countries, yet I will be to them a sanctuary for a little while in the countries where they have\ncome.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 11:17"},"“Therefore say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “I will gather you from the peoples, and assemble you out of the countries where\nyou have been scattered, and I will give you the land of Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 11:18"},"“‘They will come there, and they will take away all its detestable things and all its abominations from there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 11:19"},"I will give them one heart, and I will put a new spirit within you. I will take the stony heart out of their flesh, and\nwill give them a heart of flesh; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 11:20"},"that they may walk in my statutes, and keep my ordinances, and do them. They will be my people, and I will be their\nAllah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 11:21"},"But as for them whose heart walks after the heart of their detestable things and their abominations, I will bring their\nway on their own heads,’ says the Lord ALLAH.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 11:22"},"Then the cherubim lifted up their wings, and the wheels were beside them. The glory of Allah of Israel was over them\nabove. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 11:23"},"The LORD’s glory went up from the middle of the city, and stood on the mountain which is on the east side of the city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 11:24"},"The Spirit lifted me up, and brought me in the vision by the Spirit of Allah into Chaldea, to the captives.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["So the vision that I had seen went up from me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 11:25"},"Then I spoke to the captives all the things that the LORD had shown me.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"12","sid":"EZK 12"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 12:1"},"The LORD’s word also came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 12:2"},"“Son of man, you dwell in the middle of the rebellious house, who have eyes to see, and don’t see, who have ears to hear,\nand don’t hear; for they are a rebellious house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 12:3"},"“Therefore, you son of man, prepare your stuff for moving, and move by day in their sight. You shall move from your place\nto another place in their sight. It may be they will consider, though they are a rebellious house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 12:4"},"You shall bring out your stuff by day in their sight, as stuff for moving. You shall go out yourself at evening in their\nsight, as when men go out into exile. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 12:5"},"Dig through the wall in their sight, and carry your stuff out that way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 12:6"},"In their sight you shall bear it on your shoulder, and carry it out in the dark. You shall cover your face, so that you\ndon’t see the land, for I have set you for a sign to the house of Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 12:7"},"I did so as I was commanded. I brought out my stuff by day, as stuff for moving, and in the evening I dug through the wall\nwith my hand. I brought it out in the dark, and bore it on my shoulder in their sight.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 12:8"},"In the morning, the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 12:9"},"“Son of man, hasn’t the house of Israel, the rebellious house, said to you, ‘What are you doing?’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 12:10"},"“Say to them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “This burden concerns the prince in Jerusalem, and all the house of Israel amongst\nwhom they are.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 12:11"},"“Say, ‘I am your sign. As I have done, so will it be done to them. They will go into exile, into captivity.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 12:12"},"“‘The prince who is amongst them will bear on his shoulder in the dark, and will go out. They will dig through the wall\nto carry things out that way. He will cover his face, because he will not see the land with his eyes.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 12:13"},"I will also spread my net on him, and he will be taken in my snare. I will bring him to Babylon to the land of the\nChaldeans; yet he will not see it, though he will die there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 12:14"},"I will scatter towards every wind all who are around him to help him, and all his bands. I will draw out the sword after\nthem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 12:15"},"“‘They will know that I am the LORD when I disperse them amongst the nations, and scatter them through the countries.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 12:16"},"But I will leave a few men of them from the sword, from the famine, and from the pestilence, that they may declare all\ntheir abominations amongst the nations where they come. Then they will know that I am the LORD.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 12:17"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 12:18"},"“Son of man, eat your bread with quaking, and drink your water with trembling and with fearfulness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 12:19"},"Tell the people of the land, ‘The Lord ALLAH says concerning the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and the land of Israel: “They\nwill eat their bread with fearfulness, and drink their water in dismay, that her land may be desolate, and all that is therein,\nbecause of the violence of all those who dwell therein. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 12:20"},"The cities that are inhabited will be laid waste, and the land will be a desolation. Then you will know that I am the\nLORD.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 12:21"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 12:22"},"“Son of man, what is this proverb that you have in the land of Israel, saying, ‘The days are prolonged, and every vision\nfails?’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 12:23"},"Tell them therefore, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “I will make this proverb to cease, and they will no more use it as a proverb\nin Israel;”’ but tell them, ‘“The days are at hand, and the fulfilment of every vision.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 12:24"},"For there will be no more any false vision nor flattering divination within the house of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 12:25"},"For I am the LORD. I will speak, and the word that I speak will be performed. It will be no more deferred; for in your\ndays, rebellious house, I will speak the word, and will perform it,” says the Lord ALLAH.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 12:26"},"Again the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 12:27"},"“Son of man, behold, they of the house of Israel say, ‘The vision that he sees is for many days to come, and he\nprophesies of times that are far off.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 12:28"},"“Therefore tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “None of my words will be deferred any more, but the word which I speak will\nbe performed,” says the Lord ALLAH.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"13","sid":"EZK 13"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 13:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 13:2"},"“Son of man, prophesy against the prophets of Israel who prophesy, and say to those who prophesy out of their own heart,\n‘Hear the LORD’s word: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 13:3"},"The Lord ALLAH says, “Woe to the foolish prophets, who follow their own spirit, and have seen nothing!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 13:4"},"Israel, your prophets have been like foxes in the waste places.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 13:5"},"You have not gone up into the gaps or built up the wall for the house of Israel, to stand in the battle in the LORD’s day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 13:6"},"They have seen falsehood and lying divination, who say, ‘The LORD says;’ but the LORD has not sent them. They have made\nmen to hope that the word would be confirmed. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 13:7"},"Haven’t you seen a false vision, and haven’t you spoken a lying divination, in that you say, ‘The LORD says;’ but I have\nnot spoken?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 13:8"},"“‘Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “Because you have spoken falsehood and seen lies, therefore, behold, I am against you,”\nsays the Lord ALLAH. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 13:9"},"“My hand will be against the prophets who see false visions and who utter lying divinations. They will not be in the\ncouncil of my people, neither will they be written in the writing of the house of Israel, neither will they enter into the land\nof Israel. Then you will know that I am the Lord ALLAH.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 13:10"},"“‘Because, even because they have seduced my people, saying, “Peace;” and there is no peace. When one builds up a wall,\nbehold, they plaster it with whitewash. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 13:11"},"Tell those who plaster it with whitewash that it will fall. There will be an overflowing shower; and you, great\nhailstones, will fall. A stormy wind will tear it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 13:12"},"Behold, when the wall has fallen, won’t it be said to you, “Where is the plaster with which you have plastered it?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 13:13"},"“‘Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “I will even tear it with a stormy wind in my wrath. There will be an overflowing shower\nin my anger, and great hailstones in wrath to consume it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 13:14"},"So I will break down the wall that you have plastered with whitewash, and bring it down to the ground, so that its\nfoundation will be uncovered. It will fall, and you will be consumed in the middle of it. Then you will know that I am the\nLORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 13:15"},"Thus I will accomplish my wrath on the wall, and on those who have plastered it with whitewash. I will tell you, ‘The\nwall is no more, neither those who plastered it; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 13:16"},"to wit, the prophets of Israel who prophesy concerning Jerusalem, and who see visions of peace for her, and there is no\npeace,’” says the Lord ALLAH.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 13:17"},"You, son of man, set your face against the daughters of your people, who prophesy out of their own heart; and prophesy\nagainst them, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 13:18"},"and say, “The Lord ALLAH says: ‘Woe to the women who sew pillows on all elbows, and make kerchiefs for the head of\npersons of every stature to hunt souls! Will you hunt the souls of my people, and save souls alive for yourselves?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 13:19"},"You have profaned me amongst my people for handfuls of barley and for pieces of bread, to kill the souls who should not\ndie, and to save the souls alive who should not live, by your lying to my people who listen to lies.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 13:20"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I am against your pillows, with which you hunt the souls to make them fly, and I\nwill tear them from your arms. I will let the souls go, even the souls whom you hunt to make them fly.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 13:21"},"I will also tear your kerchiefs, and deliver my people out of your hand, and they will be no more in your hand to be\nhunted. Then you will know that I am the LORD. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 13:22"},"Because with lies you have grieved the heart of the righteous, whom I have not made sad; and strengthened the hands of\nthe wicked, that he should not return from his wicked way, and be saved alive.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 13:23"},"Therefore you shall no more see false visions, nor practise divination. I will deliver my people out of your hand. Then\nyou will know that I am the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"14","sid":"EZK 14"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 14:1"},"Then some of the elders of Israel came to me, and sat before me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 14:2"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 14:3"},"“Son of man, these men have taken their idols into their heart, and put the stumbling block of their iniquity before their\nface. Should I be enquired of at all by them? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 14:4"},"Therefore speak to them, and tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Every man of the house of Israel who takes his idols into\nhis heart, and puts the stumbling block of his iniquity before his face, and comes to the prophet; I the LORD will answer him\ntherein according to the multitude of his idols; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 14:5"},"that I may take the house of Israel in their own heart, because they are all estranged from me through their idols.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 14:6"},"“Therefore tell the house of Israel, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Return, and turn yourselves from your idols! Turn away your\nfaces from all your abominations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 14:7"},"“‘“For everyone of the house of Israel, or of the strangers who live in Israel, who separates himself from me, and takes\nhis idols into his heart, and puts the stumbling block of his iniquity before his face, and comes to the prophet to enquire for\nhimself of me; I the LORD will answer him by myself. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 14:8"},"I will set my face against that man, and will make him an astonishment, for a sign and a proverb, and I will cut him off\nfrom amongst my people. Then you will know that I am the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 14:9"},"“‘“If the prophet is deceived and speaks a word, I, the LORD, have deceived that prophet, and I will stretch out my hand\non him, and will destroy him from amongst my people Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 14:10"},"They will bear their iniquity. The iniquity of the prophet will be even as the iniquity of him who seeks him;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 14:11"},"that the house of Israel may no more go astray from me, neither defile themselves any more with all their transgressions;\nbut that they may be my people, and I may be their Allah,” says the Lord ALLAH.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 14:12"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 14:13"},"“Son of man, when a land sins against me by committing a trespass, and I stretch out my hand on it, and break the staff\nof its bread, and send famine on it, and cut off from it man and animal;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 14:14"},"though these three men, Nuh, Daniel, and Ayyub, were in it, they would deliver only their own souls by their\nrighteousness,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 14:15"},"“If I cause evil animals to pass through the land, and they ravage it, and it is made desolate, so that no man may pass\nthrough because of the animals; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 14:16"},"though these three men were in it, as I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “they would deliver neither sons nor daughters. They\nonly would be delivered, but the land would be desolate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 14:17"},"“Or if I bring a sword on that land, and say, ‘Sword, go through the land; so that I cut off from it man and animal;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 14:18"},"though these three men were in it, as I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “they would deliver neither sons nor daughters, but\nthey only would be delivered themselves. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 14:19"},"“Or if I send a pestilence into that land, and pour out my wrath on it in blood, to cut off from it man and animal;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 14:20"},"though Nuh, Daniel, and Ayyub, were in it, as I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “they would deliver neither son nor daughter;\nthey would deliver only their own souls by their righteousness.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 14:21"},"For the Lord ALLAH says: “How much more when I send my four severe judgements on Jerusalem, the sword, the famine, the\nevil animals, and the pestilence, to cut off from it man and animal!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 14:22"},"Yet, behold, there will be left a remnant in it that will be carried out, both sons and daughters. Behold, they will come\nout to you, and you will see their way and their doings. Then you will be comforted concerning the evil that I have brought on\nJerusalem, even concerning all that I have brought on it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 14:23"},"They will comfort you, when you see their way and their doings; then you will know that I have not done all that I have\ndone in it without cause,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"15","sid":"EZK 15"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 15:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 15:2"},"“Son of man, what is the vine tree more than any tree, the vine-branch which is amongst the trees of the forest?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 15:3"},"Will wood be taken of it to make anything? Will men take a pin of it to hang any vessel on it?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 15:4"},"Behold, it is cast into the fire for fuel; the fire has devoured both its ends, and the middle of it is burnt. Is it\nprofitable for any work? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 15:5"},"Behold, when it was whole, it was suitable for no work. How much less, when the fire has devoured it, and it has been\nburnt, will it yet be suitable for any work?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 15:6"},"Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “As the vine tree amongst the trees of the forest, which I have given to the fire for fuel,\nso I will give the inhabitants of Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 15:7"},"I will set my face against them. They will go out from the fire, but the fire will devour them. Then you will know that I\nam the LORD, when I set my face against them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 15:8"},"I will make the land desolate, because they have committed a trespass,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"16","sid":"EZK 16"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 16:1"},"Again the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 16:2"},"“Son of man, cause Jerusalem to know her abominations; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 16:3"},"and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says to Jerusalem: “Your origin and your birth is of the land of the Canaanite. An Amorite was\nyour father, and your mother was a Hittite. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 16:4"},"As for your birth, in the day you were born your navel was not cut. You weren’t washed in water to cleanse you. You\nweren’t salted at all, nor wrapped in blankets at all. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 16:5"},"No eye pitied you, to do any of these things to you, to have compassion on you; but you were cast out in the open field,\nbecause you were abhorred in the day that you were born. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 16:6"},"“‘“When I passed by you, and saw you wallowing in your blood, I said to you, ‘Though you are in your blood, live!’ Yes, I\nsaid to you, ‘Though you are in your blood, live!’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 16:7"},"I caused you to multiply as that which grows in the field, and you increased and grew great, and you attained to excellent\nornament. Your breasts were formed, and your hair grew; yet you were naked and bare.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 16:8"},"“‘“Now when I passed by you, and looked at you, behold, your time was the time of love; and I spread my skirt over you,\nand covered your nakedness. Yes, I swore to you, and entered into a covenant with you,” says the Lord ALLAH, “and you became\nmine. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 16:9"},"“‘“Then washed I you with water. Yes, I thoroughly washed away your blood from you, and I anointed you with oil.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 16:10"},"I clothed you also with embroidered work, and put sealskin sandals on you. I dressed you with fine linen and covered you\nwith silk. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 16:11"},"I decked you with ornaments, put bracelets on your hands, and put a chain on your neck.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 16:12"},"I put a ring on your nose, and earrings in your ears, and a beautiful crown on your head.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 16:13"},"Thus you were decked with gold and silver. Your clothing was of fine linen, silk, and embroidered work. You ate fine\nflour, honey, and oil. You were exceedingly beautiful, and you prospered to royal estate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 16:14"},"Your renown went out amongst the nations for your beauty; for it was perfect, through my majesty which I had put on you,”\nsays the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 16:15"},"“‘“But you trusted in your beauty, and played the prostitute because of your renown, and poured out your prostitution on\neveryone who passed by. It was his. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 16:16"},"You took some of your garments, and made for yourselves high places decked with various colours, and played the\nprostitute on them. This shall not happen, neither shall it be. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 16:17"},"You also took your beautiful jewels of my gold and of my silver, which I had given you, and made for yourself images of\nmen, and played the prostitute with them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 16:18"},"You took your embroidered garments, covered them, and set my oil and my incense before them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 16:19"},"My bread also which I gave you, fine flour, oil, and honey, with which I fed you, you even set it before them for a\npleasant aroma; and so it was,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 16:20"},"“‘“Moreover you have taken your sons and your daughters, whom you have borne to me, and you have sacrificed these to them\nto be devoured. Was your prostitution a small matter, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 16:21"},"that you have slain my children, and delivered them up, in causing them to pass through the fire to them?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 16:22"},"In all your abominations and your prostitution you have not remembered the days of your youth, when you were naked and\nbare, and were wallowing in your blood. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 16:23"},"“‘“It has happened after all your wickedness. Woe, woe to you!” says the Lord ALLAH,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 16:24"},"“that you have built for yourselves a vaulted place, and have made yourselves a lofty place in every street.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 16:25"},"You have built your lofty place at the head of every way, and have made your beauty an abomination, and have opened your\nfeet to everyone who passed by, and multiplied your prostitution.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 16:26"},"You have also committed sexual immorality with the Egyptians, your neighbours, great of flesh; and have multiplied your\nprostitution, to provoke me to anger. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 16:27"},"See therefore, I have stretched out my hand over you, and have diminished your portion, and delivered you to the will of\nthose who hate you, the daughters of the Philistines, who are ashamed of your lewd way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 16:28"},"You have played the prostitute also with the Assyrians, because you were insatiable; yes, you have played the prostitute\nwith them, and yet you weren’t satisfied. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 16:29"},"You have moreover multiplied your prostitution to the land of merchants, to Chaldea; and yet you weren’t satisfied with\nthis. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 16:30"},"“‘“How weak is your heart,” says the Lord ALLAH, “since you do all these things, the work of an impudent prostitute;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 16:31"},"in that you build your vaulted place at the head of every way, and make your lofty place in every street, and have not\nbeen as a prostitute, in that you scorn pay. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 16:32"},"“‘“A wife who commits adultery! Who takes strangers instead of her husband!\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 16:33"},"People give gifts to all prostitutes; but you give your gifts to all your lovers, and bribe them, that they may come to\nyou on every side for your prostitution. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 16:34"},"You are different from other women in your prostitution, in that no one follows you to play the prostitute; and whereas\nyou give hire, and no hire is given to you, therefore you are different.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 16:35"},"“Therefore, prostitute, hear the LORD’s word: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"EZK 16:36"},"‘The Lord ALLAH says, “Because your filthiness was poured out, and your nakedness uncovered through your prostitution\nwith your lovers; and because of all the idols of your abominations, and for the blood of your children, that you gave to them;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"EZK 16:37"},"therefore see, I will gather all your lovers, with whom you have taken pleasure, and all those who you have loved, with\nall those who you have hated. I will even gather them against you on every side, and will uncover your nakedness to them, that\nthey may see all your nakedness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"EZK 16:38"},"I will judge you, as women who break wedlock and shed blood are judged; and I will bring on you the blood of wrath and\njealousy. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"EZK 16:39"},"I will also give you into their hand, and they will throw down your vaulted place, and break down your lofty places. They\nwill strip you of your clothes, and take your beautiful jewels. They will leave you naked and bare.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"EZK 16:40"},"They will also bring up a company against you, and they will stone you with stones, and thrust you through with their\nswords. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"EZK 16:41"},"They will burn your houses with fire, and execute judgements on you in the sight of many women. I will cause you to cease\nfrom playing the prostitute, and you will also give no hire any more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"EZK 16:42"},"So I will cause my wrath towards you to rest, and my jealousy will depart from you. I will be quiet, and will not be\nangry any more. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"EZK 16:43"},"“‘“Because you have not remembered the days of your youth, but have raged against me in all these things; therefore,\nbehold, I also will bring your way on your head,” says the Lord ALLAH: “and you shall not commit this lewdness with all your\nabominations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"EZK 16:44"},"“‘“Behold, everyone who uses proverbs will use this proverb against you, saying, ‘As is the mother, so is her daughter.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"EZK 16:45"},"You are the daughter of your mother, who loathes her husband and her children; and you are the sister of your sisters,\nwho loathed their husbands and their children. Your mother was a Hittite, and your father an Amorite.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"EZK 16:46"},"Your elder sister is Samaria, who dwells at your left hand, she and her daughters; and your younger sister, who dwells at\nyour right hand, is Sodom with her daughters. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"EZK 16:47"},"Yet you have not walked in their ways, nor done their abominations; but soon you were more corrupt than they in all your\nways. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"EZK 16:48"},"As I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “Sodom your sister has not done, she nor her daughters, as you have done, you and your\ndaughters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"EZK 16:49"},"“‘“Behold, this was the iniquity of your sister Sodom: pride, fullness of bread, and prosperous ease was in her and in\nher daughters. She also didn’t strengthen the hand of the poor and needy.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"50","sid":"EZK 16:50"},"They were arrogant, and committed abomination before me. Therefore I took them away when I saw it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"51","sid":"EZK 16:51"},"Samaria hasn’t committed half of your sins; but you have multiplied your abominations more than they, and have justified\nyour sisters by all your abominations which you have done. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"52","sid":"EZK 16:52"},"You also bear your own shame yourself, in that you have given judgement for your sisters; through your sins that you have\ncommitted more abominable than they, they are more righteous than you. Yes, be also confounded, and bear your shame, in that\nyou have justified your sisters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"53","sid":"EZK 16:53"},"“‘“I will reverse their captivity, the captivity of Sodom and her daughters, and the captivity of Samaria and her\ndaughters, and the captivity of your captives amongst them; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"54","sid":"EZK 16:54"},"that you may bear your own shame, and may be ashamed because of all that you have done, in that you are a comfort to\nthem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"55","sid":"EZK 16:55"},"Your sisters, Sodom and her daughters, will return to their former estate; and Samaria and her daughters will return to\ntheir former estate; and you and your daughters will return to your former estate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"56","sid":"EZK 16:56"},"For your sister Sodom was not mentioned by your mouth in the day of your pride,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"57","sid":"EZK 16:57"},"before your wickedness was uncovered, as at the time of the reproach of the daughters of Syria, and of all who are around\nher, the daughters of the Philistines, who despise you all around.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"58","sid":"EZK 16:58"},"You have borne your lewdness and your abominations,” says the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"59","sid":"EZK 16:59"},"“‘For the Lord ALLAH says: “I will also deal with you as you have done, who have despised the oath in breaking the\ncovenant. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"60","sid":"EZK 16:60"},"Nevertheless I will remember my covenant with you in the days of your youth, and I will establish to you an everlasting\ncovenant. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"61","sid":"EZK 16:61"},"Then you will remember your ways and be ashamed, when you receive your sisters, your elder sisters and your younger; and\nI will give them to you for daughters, but not by your covenant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"62","sid":"EZK 16:62"},"I will establish my covenant with you. Then you will know that I am the LORD;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"63","sid":"EZK 16:63"},"that you may remember, and be confounded, and never open your mouth any more, because of your shame, when I have forgiven\nyou all that you have done,” says the Lord ALLAH.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"17","sid":"EZK 17"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 17:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 17:2"},"“Son of man, tell a riddle, and speak a parable to the house of Israel;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 17:3"},"and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “A great eagle with great wings and long feathers, full of feathers, which had various\ncolours, came to Lebanon, and took the top of the cedar. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 17:4"},"He cropped off the topmost of its young twigs, and carried it to a land of traffic. He planted it in a city of merchants.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 17:5"},"“‘“He also took some of the seed of the land, and planted it in fruitful soil. He placed it beside many waters. He set it\nas a willow tree. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 17:6"},"It grew, and became a spreading vine of low stature, whose branches turned towards him, and its roots were under him. So\nit became a vine, produced branches, and shot out sprigs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 17:7"},"“‘“There was also another great eagle with great wings and many feathers. Behold, this vine bent its roots towards him,\nand shot out its branches towards him, from the beds of its plantation, that he might water it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 17:8"},"It was planted in a good soil by many waters, that it might produce branches, and that it might bear fruit, that it might\nbe a good vine.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 17:9"},"“Say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Will it prosper? Won’t he pull up its roots, and cut off its fruit, that it may wither; that\nall its fresh springing leaves may wither? It can’t be raised from its roots by a strong arm or many people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 17:10"},"Yes, behold, being planted, will it prosper? Won’t it utterly wither when the east wind touches it? It will wither in the\nbeds where it grew.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 17:11"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 17:12"},"“Say now to the rebellious house, ‘Don’t you know what these things mean?’ Tell them, ‘Behold, the king of Babylon came\nto Jerusalem, and took its king, and its princes, and brought them to him to Babylon.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 17:13"},"He took some of the royal offspring,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["17:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or,\nseed"]}],"caller":"+"}," and made a covenant with him. He also brought him under an oath, and took away the mighty of the land;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 17:14"},"that the kingdom might be brought low, that it might not lift itself up, but that by keeping his covenant it might stand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 17:15"},"But he rebelled against him in sending his ambassadors into Egypt, that they might give him horses and many people. Will\nhe prosper? Will he who does such things escape? Will he break the covenant, and still escape?\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 17:16"},"“‘As I live,’ says the Lord ALLAH, ‘surely in the place where the king dwells who made him king, whose oath he despised,\nand whose covenant he broke, even with him in the middle of Babylon he will die.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 17:17"},"Pharaoh with his mighty army and great company won’t help him in the war, when they cast up mounds and build forts, to\ncut off many persons. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 17:18"},"For he has despised the oath by breaking the covenant; and behold, he had given his hand, and yet has done all these\nthings. He won’t escape. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 17:19"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘As I live, I will surely bring on his own head my oath that he has despised and my\ncovenant that he has broken. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 17:20"},"I will spread my net on him, and he will be taken in my snare. I will bring him to Babylon, and will enter into judgement\nwith him there for his trespass that he has trespassed against me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 17:21"},"All his fugitives in all his bands will fall by the sword, and those who remain will be scattered towards every wind.\nThen you will know that I, the LORD, have spoken it.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 17:22"},"“The Lord ALLAH says: ‘I will also take some of the lofty top of the cedar, and will plant it. I will crop off from the\ntopmost of its young twigs a tender one, and I will plant it on a high and lofty mountain.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 17:23"},"I will plant it in the mountain of the height of Israel; and it will produce boughs, and bear fruit, and be a good cedar.\nBirds of every kind will dwell in the shade of its branches. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 17:24"},"All the trees of the field will know that I, the LORD, have brought down the high tree, have exalted the low tree, have\ndried up the green tree, and have made the dry tree flourish. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“‘I, the LORD, have spoken and have done it.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"18","sid":"EZK 18"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 18:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me again, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 18:2"},"“What do you mean, that you use this proverb concerning the land of Israel, saying,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘The fathers have eaten sour grapes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the children’s teeth are set on edge’? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 18:3"},"“As I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “you shall not use this proverb any more in Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 18:4"},"Behold, all souls are mine; as the soul of the father, so also the soul of the son is mine. The soul who sins, he shall\ndie. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 18:5"},"“But if a man is just, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and does that which is lawful and right, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 18:6"},"and has not eaten on the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hasn’t lifted up his eyes to the idols of the house of Israel,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["hasn’t defiled his neighbour’s wife, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hasn’t come near a woman in her impurity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 18:7"},"and has not wronged any, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but has restored to the debtor his pledge, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["has taken nothing by robbery, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has given his bread to the hungry, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has covered the naked with a garment; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 18:8"},"he who hasn’t lent to them with interest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hasn’t taken any increase from them, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["who has withdrawn his hand from iniquity, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has executed true justice between man and man, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 18:9"},"has walked in my statutes, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has kept my ordinances, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to deal truly; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["he is just, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["he shall surely live,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 18:10"},"“If he fathers a son who is a robber who sheds blood, and who does any one of these things,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 18:11"},"or who does not do any of those things, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["but even has eaten at the mountain shrines, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and defiled his neighbour’s wife, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 18:12"},"has wronged the poor and needy, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has taken by robbery, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["has not restored the pledge, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has lifted up his eyes to the idols, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has committed abomination, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 18:13"},"has lent with interest, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has taken increase from the poor; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["shall he then live? He shall not live. He has done all these abominations. He shall surely die. His blood will be on him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 18:14"},"“Now, behold, if he fathers a son, who sees all his father’s sins, which he has done, and fears, and does not such like;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 18:15"},"who hasn’t eaten on the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hasn’t lifted up his eyes to the idols of the house of Israel,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hasn’t defiled his neighbour’s wife, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 18:16"},"hasn’t wronged any, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["hasn’t taken anything to pledge, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["hasn’t taken by robbery, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["but has given his bread to the hungry, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and has covered the naked with a garment; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 18:17"},"who has withdrawn his hand from the poor, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who hasn’t received interest or increase, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["has executed my ordinances, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["has walked in my statutes; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["he shall not die for the iniquity of his father. He shall surely live.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 18:18"},"As for his father, because he cruelly oppressed, robbed his brother, and did that which is not good amongst his people,\nbehold, he will die in his iniquity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 18:19"},"“Yet you say, ‘Why doesn’t the son bear the iniquity of the father?’ When the son has done that which is lawful and\nright, and has kept all my statutes, and has done them, he will surely live.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 18:20"},"The soul who sins, he shall die. The son shall not bear the iniquity of the father, neither shall the father bear the\niniquity of the son. The righteousness of the righteous shall be on him, and the wickedness of the wicked shall be on him.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 18:21"},"“But if the wicked turns from all his sins that he has committed, and keeps all my statutes, and does that which is\nlawful and right, he shall surely live. He shall not die. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 18:22"},"None of his transgressions that he has committed will be remembered against him. In his righteousness that he has done,\nhe shall live. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 18:23"},"Have I any pleasure in the death of the wicked?” says the Lord ALLAH; “and not rather that he should return from his way,\nand live? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 18:24"},"“But when the righteous turns away from his righteousness, and commits iniquity, and does according to all the\nabominations that the wicked man does, should he live? None of his righteous deeds that he has done will be remembered. In his\ntrespass that he has trespassed, and in his sin that he has sinned, in them he shall die.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 18:25"},"“Yet you say, ‘The way of the Lord is not equal.’ Hear now, house of Israel: Is my way not equal? Aren’t your ways\nunequal? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 18:26"},"When the righteous man turns away from his righteousness, and commits iniquity, and dies therein; in his iniquity that he\nhas done he shall die. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 18:27"},"Again, when the wicked man turns away from his wickedness that he has committed, and does that which is lawful and right,\nhe will save his soul alive. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 18:28"},"Because he considers, and turns away from all his transgressions that he has committed, he shall surely live. He shall\nnot die. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 18:29"},"Yet the house of Israel says, ‘The way of the Lord is not fair.’ House of Israel, aren’t my ways fair? Aren’t your ways\nunfair? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 18:30"},"“Therefore I will judge you, house of Israel, everyone according to his ways,” says the Lord ALLAH. “Return, and turn\nyourselves from all your transgressions; so iniquity will not be your ruin.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 18:31"},"Cast away from you all your transgressions, in which you have transgressed; and make yourself a new heart and a new\nspirit: for why will you die, house of Israel? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 18:32"},"For I have no pleasure in the death of him who dies,” says the Lord ALLAH. “Therefore turn yourselves, and live!\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"19","sid":"EZK 19"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 19:1"},"“Moreover, take up a lamentation for the princes of Israel,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 19:2"},"and say, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘What was your mother? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["A lioness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["She couched amongst lions, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the middle of the young lions she nourished her cubs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 19:3"},"She brought up one of her cubs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He became a young lion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He learnt to catch the prey. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He devoured men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 19:4"},"The nations also heard of him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He was taken in their pit; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they brought him with hooks to the land of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 19:5"},"“‘Now when she saw that she had waited, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her hope was lost, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["then she took another of her cubs, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and made him a young lion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 19:6"},"He went up and down amongst the lions. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He became a young lion. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["He learnt to catch the prey. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He devoured men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 19:7"},"He knew their palaces, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and laid waste their cities. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The land was desolate, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with its fullness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["because of the noise of his roaring. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 19:8"},"Then the nations attacked him on every side from the provinces.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They spread their net over him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["He was taken in their pit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 19:9"},"They put him in a cage with hooks, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and brought him to the king of Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They brought him into strongholds, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that his voice should no more be heard on the mountains of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 19:10"},"“‘Your mother was like a vine \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in your blood, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["planted by the waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It was fruitful and full of branches by reason of many waters.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 19:11"},"It had strong branches for the sceptres of those who ruled.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Their stature was exalted amongst the thick boughs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They were seen in their height \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the multitude of their branches. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 19:12"},"But it was plucked up in fury. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It was cast down to the ground, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and the east wind dried up its fruit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Its strong branches were broken off and withered. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The fire consumed them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 19:13"},"Now it is planted in the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in a dry and thirsty land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 19:14"},"Fire has gone out of its branches. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It has devoured its fruit, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that there is in it no strong branch to be a sceptre to rule.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["This is a lamentation, and shall be for a lamentation.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"20","sid":"EZK 20"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 20:1"},"In the seventh year, in the fifth month, the tenth day of the month, some of the elders of Israel came to enquire of the\nLORD, and sat before me. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 20:2"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 20:3"},"“Son of man, speak to the elders of Israel, and tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Is it to enquire of me that you have\ncome? As I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “I will not be enquired of by you.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 20:4"},"“Will you judge them, son of man? Will you judge them? Cause them to know the abominations of their fathers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 20:5"},"Tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “In the day when I chose Israel, and swore to the offspring of the house of Yaqub, and\nmade myself known to them in the land of Egypt, when I swore to them, saying, ‘I am Allah your LORD;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 20:6"},"in that day I swore to them, to bring them out of the land of Egypt into a land that I had searched out for them, flowing\nwith milk and honey, which is the glory of all lands. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 20:7"},"I said to them, ‘Each of you throw away the abominations of his eyes. Don’t defile yourselves with the idols of Egypt. I\nam Allah your LORD.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 20:8"},"“‘“But they rebelled against me, and would not listen to me. They didn’t all throw away the abominations of their eyes.\nThey also didn’t forsake the idols of Egypt. Then I said I would pour out my wrath on them, to accomplish my anger against them\nin the middle of the land of Egypt. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 20:9"},"But I worked for my name’s sake, that it should not be profaned in the sight of the nations, amongst which they were, in\nwhose sight I made myself known to them, in bringing them out of the land of Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 20:10"},"So I caused them to go out of the land of Egypt, and brought them into the wilderness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 20:11"},"I gave them my statutes, and showed them my ordinances, which if a man does, he will live in them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 20:12"},"Moreover also I gave them my Sabbaths, to be a sign between me and them, that they might know that I am the LORD who\nsanctifies them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 20:13"},"“‘“But the house of Israel rebelled against me in the wilderness. They didn’t walk in my statutes, and they rejected my\nordinances, which if a man keeps, he shall live in them. They greatly profaned my Sabbaths. Then I said I would pour out my\nwrath on them in the wilderness, to consume them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 20:14"},"But I worked for my name’s sake, that it should not be profaned in the sight of the nations, in whose sight I brought\nthem out. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 20:15"},"Moreover also I swore to them in the wilderness, that I would not bring them into the land which I had given them,\nflowing with milk and honey, which is the glory of all lands; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 20:16"},"because they rejected my ordinances, and didn’t walk in my statutes, and profaned my Sabbaths; for their heart went after\ntheir idols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 20:17"},"Nevertheless my eye spared them, and I didn’t destroy them. I didn’t make a full end of them in the wilderness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 20:18"},"I said to their children in the wilderness, ‘Don’t walk in the statutes of your fathers. Don’t observe their ordinances\nor defile yourselves with their idols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 20:19"},"I am Allah your LORD. Walk in my statutes, keep my ordinances, and do them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 20:20"},"Make my Sabbaths holy. They shall be a sign between me and you, that you may know that I am Allah your LORD.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 20:21"},"“‘“But the children rebelled against me. They didn’t walk in my statutes, and didn’t keep my ordinances to do them, which\nif a man does, he shall live in them. They profaned my Sabbaths. Then I said I would pour out my wrath on them, to accomplish\nmy anger against them in the wilderness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 20:22"},"Nevertheless I withdrew my hand, and worked for my name’s sake, that it should not be profaned in the sight of the\nnations, in whose sight I brought them out. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 20:23"},"Moreover I swore to them in the wilderness, that I would scatter them amongst the nations, and disperse them through the\ncountries; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 20:24"},"because they had not executed my ordinances, but had rejected my statutes, and had profaned my Sabbaths, and their eyes\nwere after their fathers’ idols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 20:25"},"Moreover also I gave them statutes that were not good, and ordinances in which they should not live.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 20:26"},"I polluted them in their own gifts, in that they caused all that opens the womb to pass through the fire, that I might\nmake them desolate, to the end that they might know that I am the LORD.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 20:27"},"“Therefore, son of man, speak to the house of Israel, and tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Moreover, in this your\nfathers have blasphemed me, in that they have committed a trespass against me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 20:28"},"For when I had brought them into the land which I swore to give to them, then they saw every high hill, and every thick\ntree, and they offered there their sacrifices, and there they presented the provocation of their offering. There they also made\ntheir pleasant aroma, and there they poured out their drink offerings.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 20:29"},"Then I said to them, ‘What does the high place where you go mean?’ So its name is called\nBamah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["20:29 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["“Bamah” means “High Place”."]}],"caller":"+"}," to this day.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 20:30"},"“Therefore tell the house of Israel, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Do you pollute yourselves in the way of your fathers? Do you\nplay the prostitute after their abominations? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 20:31"},"When you offer your gifts, when you make your sons pass through the fire, do you pollute yourselves with all your idols\nto this day? Should I be enquired of by you, house of Israel? As I live, says the Lord ALLAH, I will not be enquired of by you!\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 20:32"},"“‘“That which comes into your mind will not be at all, in that you say, ‘We will be as the nations, as the families of\nthe countries, to serve wood and stone.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 20:33"},"As I live, says the Lord ALLAH, surely with a mighty hand, with an outstretched arm, and with wrath poured out, I will be\nking over you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 20:34"},"I will bring you out from the peoples, and will gather you out of the countries in which you are scattered with a mighty\nhand, with an outstretched arm, and with wrath poured out. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 20:35"},"I will bring you into the wilderness of the peoples, and there I will enter into judgement with you face to face.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"EZK 20:36"},"Just as I entered into judgement with your fathers in the wilderness of the land of Egypt, so I will enter into judgement\nwith you,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"EZK 20:37"},"“I will cause you to pass under the rod, and I will bring you into the bond of the covenant.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"EZK 20:38"},"I will purge out from amongst you the rebels and those who disobey me. I will bring them out of the land where they live,\nbut they shall not enter into the land of Israel. Then you will know that I am the LORD.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"EZK 20:39"},"“‘As for you, house of Israel, the Lord ALLAH says: “Go, everyone serve his idols, and hereafter also, if you will not\nlisten to me; but you shall no more profane my holy name with your gifts and with your idols.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"EZK 20:40"},"For in my holy mountain, in the mountain of the height of Israel,” says the Lord ALLAH, “there all the house of Israel,\nall of them, shall serve me in the land. There I will accept them, and there I will require your offerings and the first fruits\nof your offerings, with all your holy things. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"EZK 20:41"},"I will accept you as a pleasant aroma when I bring you out from the peoples and gather you out of the countries in which\nyou have been scattered. I will be sanctified in you in the sight of the nations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"EZK 20:42"},"You will know that I am the LORD when I bring you into the land of Israel, into the country which I swore to give to your\nfathers. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"EZK 20:43"},"There you will remember your ways, and all your deeds in which you have polluted yourselves. Then you will loathe\nyourselves in your own sight for all your evils that you have committed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"EZK 20:44"},"You will know that I am the LORD, when I have dealt with you for my name’s sake, not according to your evil ways, nor\naccording to your corrupt doings, you house of Israel,” says the Lord ALLAH.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"EZK 20:45"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"EZK 20:46"},"“Son of man, set your face towards the south, and preach towards the south, and prophesy against the forest of the field\nin the South. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"EZK 20:47"},"Tell the forest of the South, ‘Hear the LORD’s word: The Lord ALLAH says, “Behold, I will kindle a fire in you, and it\nwill devour every green tree in you, and every dry tree. The burning flame will not be quenched, and all faces from the south\nto the north will be burnt by it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"EZK 20:48"},"All flesh will see that I, the LORD, have kindled it. It will not be quenched.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"EZK 20:49"},"Then I said, “Ah Lord ALLAH! They say of me, ‘Isn’t he a speaker of parables?’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"21","sid":"EZK 21"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 21:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 21:2"},"“Son of man, set your face towards Jerusalem, and preach towards the sanctuaries, and prophesy against the land of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 21:3"},"Tell the land of Israel, ‘The LORD says: “Behold, I am against you, and will draw my sword out of its sheath, and will cut\noff from you the righteous and the wicked. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 21:4"},"Seeing then that I will cut off from you the righteous and the wicked, therefore my sword will go out of its sheath\nagainst all flesh from the south to the north. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 21:5"},"All flesh will know that I, the LORD, have drawn my sword out of its sheath. It will not return any more.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 21:6"},"“Therefore sigh, you son of man. You shall sigh before their eyes with a broken\nheart",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:6 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["literally, the breaking of your thighs"]}],"caller":"+"}," and with bitterness.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 21:7"},"It shall be, when they ask you, ‘Why do you sigh?’ that you shall say, ‘Because of the news, for it comes! Every heart\nwill melt, all hands will be feeble, every spirit will faint, and all knees will be weak as water. Behold, it comes, and it\nshall be done, says the Lord ALLAH.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 21:8"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 21:9"},"“Son of man, prophesy, and say, ‘The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A sword! A sword! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is sharpened, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and also polished. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 21:10"},"It is sharpened that it may make a slaughter. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is polished that it may be as lightning. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Should we then make mirth? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The rod of my son condemns every tree. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 21:11"},"It is given to be polished, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that it may be handled. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The sword is sharpened. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, it is polished \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to give it into the hand of the killer.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 21:12"},"Cry and wail, son of man; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for it is on my people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is on all the princes of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They are delivered over to the sword with my people. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Therefore beat your thigh. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 21:13"},"“For there is a trial. What if even the rod that condemns will be no more?” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 21:14"},"“You therefore, son of man, prophesy, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and strike your hands together. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Let the sword be doubled the third time, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the sword of the fatally wounded. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It is the sword of the great one who is fatally wounded, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which enters into their rooms. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 21:15"},"I have set the threatening sword against all their gates, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that their heart may melt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their stumblings be multiplied. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Ah! It is made as lightning. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is pointed for slaughter. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 21:16"},"Gather yourselves together. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Go to the right. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Set yourselves in array. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Go to the left, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["wherever your face is set. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 21:17"},"I will also strike my hands together, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will cause my wrath to rest. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I, the LORD, have spoken it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 21:18"},"The LORD’s word came to me again, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 21:19"},"“Also, you son of man, appoint two ways, that the sword of the king of Babylon may come. They both will come out of one\nland, and mark out a place. Marqus it out at the head of the way to the city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 21:20"},"You shall appoint a way for the sword to come to Rabbah of the children of Ammon, and to Judah in Jerusalem the\nfortified. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 21:21"},"For the king of Babylon stood at the parting of the way, at the head of the two ways, to use divination. He shook the\narrows back and forth. He consulted the teraphim.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["21:21\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["teraphim were household idols that may have been associated with inheritance rights to the household\nproperty."]}],"caller":"+"}," He looked in the liver. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 21:22"},"In his right hand was the lot for Jerusalem, to set battering rams, to open the mouth in the slaughter, to lift up the\nvoice with shouting, to set battering rams against the gates, to cast up mounds, and to build forts.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 21:23"},"It will be to them as a false divination in their sight, who have sworn oaths to them; but he brings iniquity to memory,\nthat they may be taken. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 21:24"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Because you have caused your iniquity to be remembered, in that your transgressions are\nuncovered, so that in all your doings your sins appear; because you have come to memory, you will be taken with the hand.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 21:25"},"“‘You, deadly wounded wicked one, the prince of Israel, whose day has come, in the time of the iniquity of the end,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 21:26"},"the Lord ALLAH says: “Remove the turban, and take off the crown. This will not be as it was. Exalt that which is low, and\nhumble that which is high. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 21:27"},"I will overturn, overturn, overturn it. This also will be no more, until he comes whose right it is; and I will give\nit.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 21:28"},"“You, son of man, prophesy, and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says this concerning the children of Ammon, and concerning their\nreproach: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“A sword! A sword is drawn! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It is polished for the slaughter, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to cause it to devour, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that it may be as lightning; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 21:29"},"while they see for you false visions, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["while they divine lies to you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["to lay you on the necks of the wicked who are deadly wounded,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["whose day has come in the time of the iniquity of the end. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 21:30"},"Cause it to return into its sheath. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["In the place where you were created, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the land of your birth, I will judge you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 21:31"},"I will pour out my indignation on you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will blow on you with the fire of my wrath. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will deliver you into the hand of brutish men, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["skilful to destroy. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 21:32"},"You will be for fuel to the fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your blood will be in the middle of the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You will be remembered no more; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I, the LORD, have spoken it.”’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"22","sid":"EZK 22"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 22:1"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 22:2"},"“You, son of man, will you judge? Will you judge the bloody city? Then cause her to know all her abominations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 22:3"},"You shall say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “A city that sheds blood within herself, that her time may come, and that makes idols\nagainst herself to defile her! \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 22:4"},"You have become guilty in your blood that you have shed, and are defiled in your idols which you have made! You have\ncaused your days to draw near, and have come even to your years. Therefore I have made you a reproach to the nations, and a\nmocking to all the countries. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 22:5"},"Those who are near, and those who are far from you, will mock you, you infamous one, full of tumult.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 22:6"},"“‘“Behold, the princes of Israel, everyone according to his power, have been in you to shed blood.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 22:7"},"In you have they treated father and mother with contempt.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["22:7 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Literally, "]},{"type":"char","marker":"fqa","content":["made light of father and mother."]}],"caller":"+"}," Amongst you they have oppressed the foreigner. In you they\nhave wronged the fatherless and the widow. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 22:8"},"You have despised my holy things, and have profaned my Sabbaths.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 22:9"},"Slanderous men have been in you to shed blood. In you they have eaten on the mountains. They have committed lewdness\namongst you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 22:10"},"In you have they uncovered their fathers’ nakedness. In you have they humbled her who was unclean in her impurity.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 22:11"},"One has committed abomination with his neighbour’s wife; and another has lewdly defiled his daughter-in-law. Another in\nyou has humbled his sister, his father’s daughter. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 22:12"},"In you have they taken bribes to shed blood. You have taken interest and increase, and you have greedily gained of your\nneighbours by oppression, and have forgotten me,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 22:13"},"“‘“Behold, therefore I have struck my hand at your dishonest gain which you have made, and at your blood which has been\nwithin you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 22:14"},"Can your heart endure, or can your hands be strong, in the days that I will deal with you? I, the LORD, have spoken it,\nand will do it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 22:15"},"I will scatter you amongst the nations, and disperse you through the countries. I will consume your filthiness out of\nyou. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 22:16"},"You will be profaned in yourself, in the sight of the nations. Then you will know that I am the LORD.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 22:17"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 22:18"},"“Son of man, the house of Israel has become dross to me. All of them are bronze, tin, iron, and lead in the middle of the\nfurnace. They are the dross of silver. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 22:19"},"Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Because you have all become dross, therefore, behold, I will gather you into the middle\nof Jerusalem. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 22:20"},"As they gather silver, bronze, iron, lead, and tin into the middle of the furnace, to blow the fire on it, to melt it; so\nI will gather you in my anger and in my wrath, and I will lay you there, and melt you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 22:21"},"Yes, I will gather you, and blow on you with the fire of my wrath, and you will be melted in the middle of it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 22:22"},"As silver is melted in the middle of the furnace, so you will be melted in the middle of it; and you will know that I,\nthe LORD, have poured out my wrath on you.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 22:23"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 22:24"},"“Son of man, tell her, ‘You are a land that is not cleansed, nor rained on in the day of indignation.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 22:25"},"There is a conspiracy of her prophets within it, like a roaring lion ravening the prey. They have devoured souls. They\ntake treasure and precious things. They have made many widows within it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 22:26"},"Her priests have done violence to my law, and have profaned my holy things. They have made no distinction between the\nholy and the common, neither have they caused men to discern between the unclean and the clean, and have hidden their eyes from\nmy Sabbaths. So I am profaned amongst them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 22:27"},"Her princes within it are like wolves ravening the prey, to shed blood, and to destroy souls, that they may get dishonest\ngain. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 22:28"},"Her prophets have plastered for them with whitewash, seeing false visions, and divining lies to them, saying, ‘The Lord\nALLAH says,’ when the LORD has not spoken. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 22:29"},"The people of the land have used oppression and exercised robbery. Yes, they have troubled the poor and needy, and have\noppressed the foreigner wrongfully. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 22:30"},"“I sought for a man amongst them who would build up the wall and stand in the gap before me for the land, that I would\nnot destroy it; but I found no one. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 22:31"},"Therefore I have poured out my indignation on them. I have consumed them with the fire of my wrath. I have brought their\nown way on their heads,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"23","sid":"EZK 23"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 23:1"},"The LORD’s word came again to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 23:2"},"“Son of man, there were two women, the daughters of one mother.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 23:3"},"They played the prostitute in Egypt. They played the prostitute in their youth. Their breasts were fondled there, and\ntheir youthful nipples were caressed there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 23:4"},"Their names were Oholah the elder, and Oholibah her sister. They became mine, and they bore sons and daughters. As for\ntheir names, Samaria is Oholah, and Jerusalem Oholibah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 23:5"},"“Oholah played the prostitute when she was mine. She doted on her lovers, on the Assyrians her neighbours,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 23:6"},"who were clothed with blue, governors and rulers, all of them desirable young men, horsemen riding on horses.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 23:7"},"She gave herself as a prostitute to them, all of them the choicest men of Assyria. She defiled herself with the idols of\nwhoever she lusted after. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 23:8"},"She hasn’t left her prostitution since leaving Egypt; for in her youth they lay with her. They caressed her youthful\nnipples; and they poured out their prostitution on her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 23:9"},"“Therefore I delivered her into the hand of her lovers, into the hand of the Assyrians, on whom she doted.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 23:10"},"These uncovered her nakedness. They took her sons and her daughters; and they killed her with the sword. She became a\nbyword amongst women; for they executed judgements on her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 23:11"},"“Her sister Oholibah saw this, yet she was more corrupt in her lusting than she, and in her prostitution which was more\ndepraved than the prostitution of her sister. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 23:12"},"She lusted after the Assyrians, governors and rulers, her neighbours, clothed most gorgeously, horsemen riding on horses,\nall of them desirable young men. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 23:13"},"I saw that she was defiled. They both went the same way. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 23:14"},"“She increased her prostitution; for she saw men portrayed on the wall, the images of the Chaldeans portrayed with red,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 23:15"},"dressed with belts on their waists, with flowing turbans on their heads, all of them looking like princes, after the\nlikeness of the Babylonians in Chaldea, the land of their birth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 23:16"},"As soon as she saw them, she lusted after them and sent messengers to them into Chaldea.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 23:17"},"The Babylonians came to her into the bed of love, and they defiled her with their prostitution. She was polluted with\nthem, and her soul was alienated from them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 23:18"},"So she uncovered her prostitution and uncovered her nakedness. Then my soul was alienated from her, just like my soul was\nalienated from her sister. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 23:19"},"Yet she multiplied her prostitution, remembering the days of her youth, in which she had played the prostitute in the\nland of Egypt. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 23:20"},"She lusted after their lovers, whose flesh is as the flesh of donkeys, and whose issue is like the issue of horses.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 23:21"},"Thus you called to memory the lewdness of your youth, in the caressing of your nipples by the Egyptians because of your\nyouthful breasts. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 23:22"},"“Therefore, Oholibah, the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I will raise up your lovers against you, from whom your soul is\nalienated, and I will bring them against you on every side: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 23:23"},"the Babylonians and all the Chaldeans, Pekod, Shoa, Koa, and all the Assyrians with them; all of them desirable young\nmen, governors and rulers, princes and men of renown, all of them riding on horses.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 23:24"},"They will come against you with weapons, chariots, and wagons, and with a company of peoples. They will set themselves\nagainst you with buckler, shield, and helmet all around. I will commit the judgement to them, and they will judge you according\nto their judgements. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 23:25"},"I will set my jealousy against you, and they will deal with you in fury. They will take away your nose and your ears.\nYour remnant will fall by the sword. They will take your sons and your daughters; and the rest of you will be devoured by the\nfire. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 23:26"},"They will also strip you of your clothes, and take away your beautiful jewels.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 23:27"},"Thus I will make your lewdness to cease from you, and remove your prostitution from the land of Egypt; so that you will\nnot lift up your eyes to them, nor remember Egypt any more.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 23:28"},"“For the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I will deliver you into the hand of them whom you hate, into the hand of them from\nwhom your soul is alienated. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 23:29"},"They will deal with you in hatred, and will take away all your labour, and will leave you naked and bare. The nakedness\nof your prostitution will be uncovered, both your lewdness and your prostitution.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 23:30"},"These things will be done to you, because you have played the prostitute after the nations, and because you are polluted\nwith their idols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 23:31"},"You have walked in the way of your sister; therefore I will give her cup into your hand.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 23:32"},"“The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘You will drink of your sister’s cup, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["which is deep and large. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You will be ridiculed and held in derision. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It contains much. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 23:33"},"You will be filled with drunkenness and sorrow, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the cup of astonishment and desolation, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the cup of your sister Samaria. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 23:34"},"You will even drink it and drain it out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will gnaw the broken pieces of it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will tear your breasts; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":["for I have spoken it,’ says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 23:35"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Because you have forgotten me, and cast me behind your back, therefore you also bear\nyour lewdness and your prostitution.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"EZK 23:36"},"The LORD said moreover to me: “Son of man, will you judge Oholah and Oholibah? Then declare to them their abominations.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"EZK 23:37"},"For they have committed adultery, and blood is in their hands. They have committed adultery with their idols. They have\nalso caused their sons, whom they bore to me, to pass through the fire to them to be devoured.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"EZK 23:38"},"Moreover this they have done to me: they have defiled my sanctuary in the same day, and have profaned my Sabbaths.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"EZK 23:39"},"For when they had slain their children to their idols, then they came the same day into my sanctuary to profane it; and\nbehold, they have done this in the middle of my house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"EZK 23:40"},"“Furthermore you sisters have sent for men who come from far away, to whom a messenger was sent, and behold, they came;\nfor whom you washed yourself, painted your eyes, decorated yourself with ornaments,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"EZK 23:41"},"and sat on a stately bed, with a table prepared before it, whereupon you set my incense and my oil.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"EZK 23:42"},"“The voice of a multitude being at ease was with her. With men of the common sort were brought drunkards from the\nwilderness; and they put bracelets on their hands, and beautiful crowns on their heads.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"EZK 23:43"},"Then I said of her who was old in adulteries, ‘Now they will play the prostitute with her, and she with them.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"EZK 23:44"},"They went in to her, as they go in to a prostitute. So they went in to Oholah and to Oholibah, the lewd women.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"EZK 23:45"},"Righteous men will judge them with the judgement of adulteresses and with the judgement of women who shed blood; because\nthey are adulteresses, and blood is in their hands. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"EZK 23:46"},"“For the Lord ALLAH says: ‘I will bring up a mob against them, and will give them to be tossed back and forth and robbed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"EZK 23:47"},"The company will stone them with stones, and dispatch them with their swords. They will kill their sons and their\ndaughters, and burn up their houses with fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"EZK 23:48"},"“‘Thus I will cause lewdness to cease out of the land, that all women may be taught not to be lewd like you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"EZK 23:49"},"They will recompense your lewdness on you, and you will bear the sins of your idols. Then you will know that I am the\nLord ALLAH.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"24","sid":"EZK 24"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 24:1"},"Again, in the ninth year, in the tenth month, in the tenth day of the month, the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 24:2"},"“Son of man, write the name of the day, this same day. The king of Babylon drew close to Jerusalem this same day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 24:3"},"Utter a parable to the rebellious house, and tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Put the cauldron on the fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Put it on, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and also pour water into it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 24:4"},"Gather its pieces into it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even every good piece: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the thigh and the shoulder. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Fill it with the choice bones. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 24:5"},"Take the choice of the flock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and also a pile of wood for the bones under the cauldron. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Make it boil well. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, let its bones be boiled within it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 24:6"},"“‘Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Woe to the bloody city, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to the cauldron whose rust is in it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and whose rust hasn’t gone out of it! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Take out of it piece after piece. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["No lot is fallen on it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 24:7"},"“‘“For her blood is in the middle of her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["She set it on the bare rock. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["She didn’t pour it on the ground, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to cover it with dust. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 24:8"},"That it may cause wrath to come up to take vengeance, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have set her blood on the bare rock, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that it should not be covered.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"m","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 24:9"},"“‘Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Woe to the bloody city! \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I also will make the pile great. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 24:10"},"Heap on the wood. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Make the fire hot. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Boil the meat well. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Make the broth thick, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and let the bones be burnt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 24:11"},"Then set it empty on its coals, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that it may be hot, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and its bronze may burn, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and that its filthiness may be molten in it, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that its rust may be consumed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 24:12"},"She is weary with toil; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet her great rust, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["rust by fire, doesn’t leave her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 24:13"},"“‘“In your filthiness is lewdness. Because I have cleansed you and you weren’t cleansed, you won’t be cleansed from your\nfilthiness any more, until I have caused my wrath towards you to rest.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 24:14"},"I, the LORD, have spoken it. It will happen, and I will do it. I won’t go back. I won’t spare. I won’t repent. According\nto your ways, and according to your doings, they will judge you,” says the Lord ALLAH.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 24:15"},"Also the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 24:16"},"“Son of man, behold, I will take away from you the desire of your eyes with a stroke: yet you shall neither mourn nor\nweep, neither shall your tears run down. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 24:17"},"Sigh, but not aloud. Make no mourning for the dead. Bind your headdress on you, and put your sandals on your feet. Don’t\ncover your lips, and don’t eat mourner’s bread.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 24:18"},"So I spoke to the people in the morning; and at evening my wife died. So I did in the morning as I was commanded.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 24:19"},"The people asked me, “Won’t you tell us what these things are to us, that you do so?”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 24:20"},"Then I said to them, “The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 24:21"},"‘Speak to the house of Israel, “The Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I will profane my sanctuary, the pride of your power, the\ndesire of your eyes, and that which your soul pities; and your sons and your daughters whom you have left behind will fall by\nthe sword. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 24:22"},"You will do as I have done. You won’t cover your lips or eat mourner’s bread.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 24:23"},"Your turbans will be on your heads, and your sandals on your feet. You won’t mourn or weep; but you will pine away in\nyour iniquities, and moan one towards another. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 24:24"},"Thus Ezekiel will be a sign to you; according to all that he has done, you will do. When this comes, then you will know\nthat I am the Lord ALLAH.’”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 24:25"},"“You, son of man, shouldn’t it be in the day when I take from them their strength, the joy of their glory, the desire of\ntheir eyes, and that whereupon they set their heart, their sons and their daughters,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 24:26"},"that in that day he who escapes will come to you, to cause you to hear it with your ears?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 24:27"},"In that day your mouth will be opened to him who has escaped, and you will speak, and be no more mute. So you will be a\nsign to them. Then they will know that I am the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"25","sid":"EZK 25"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 25:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 25:2"},"“Son of man, set your face towards the children of Ammon, and prophesy against them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 25:3"},"Tell the children of Ammon, ‘Hear the word of the Lord ALLAH! The Lord ALLAH says, “Because you said, ‘Aha!’ against my\nsanctuary, when it was profaned; and against the land of Israel, when it was made desolate; and against the house of Judah,\nwhen they went into captivity: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 25:4"},"therefore, behold, I will deliver you to the children of the east for a possession. They will set their encampments in\nyou, and make their dwellings in you. They will eat your fruit and they will drink your milk.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 25:5"},"I will make Rabbah a stable for camels, and the children of Ammon a resting place for flocks. Then you will know that I am\nthe LORD.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 25:6"},"For the Lord ALLAH says: “Because you have clapped your hands, stamped with the feet, and rejoiced with all the contempt\nof your soul against the land of Israel; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 25:7"},"therefore, behold, I have stretched out my hand on you, and will deliver you for a plunder to the nations. I will cut you\noff from the peoples, and I will cause you to perish out of the countries. I will destroy you. Then you will know that I am the\nLORD.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 25:8"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Because Moab and Seir say, ‘Behold, the house of Judah is like all the nations;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 25:9"},"therefore, behold, I will open the side of Moab from the cities, from his cities which are on his frontiers, the glory of\nthe country, Beth Jeshimoth, Baal Meon, and Kiriathaim, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 25:10"},"to the children of the east, to go against the children of Ammon; and I will give them for a possession, that the\nchildren of Ammon may not be remembered amongst the nations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 25:11"},"I will execute judgements on Moab. Then they will know that I am the LORD.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 25:12"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Because Edom has dealt against the house of Judah by taking vengeance, and has greatly offended,\nand taken revenge on them;” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 25:13"},"therefore the Lord ALLAH says, “I will stretch out my hand on Edom, and will cut off man and animal from it; and I will\nmake it desolate from Teman. They will fall by the sword even to Dedan.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 25:14"},"I will lay my vengeance on Edom by the hand of my people Israel. They will do in Edom according to my anger and according\nto my wrath. Then they will know my vengeance,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 25:15"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Because the Philistines have taken revenge, and have taken vengeance with contempt of soul to\ndestroy with perpetual hostility;” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 25:16"},"therefore the Lord ALLAH says, “Behold, I will stretch out my hand on the Philistines, and I will cut off the\nCherethites, and destroy the remnant of the sea coast. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 25:17"},"I will execute great vengeance on them with wrathful rebukes. Then they will know that I am the LORD, when I lay my\nvengeance on them.”’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"26","sid":"EZK 26"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 26:1"},"In the eleventh year, in the first of the month, the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 26:2"},"“Son of man, because Tyre has said against Jerusalem, ‘Aha! She is broken! She who was the gateway of the peoples has been\nreturned to me. I will be replenished, now that she is laid waste;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 26:3"},"therefore the Lord ALLAH says, ‘Behold, I am against you, Tyre, and will cause many nations to come up against you, as the\nsea causes its waves to come up. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 26:4"},"They will destroy the walls of Tyre, and break down her towers. I will also scrape her dust from her, and make her a bare\nrock. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 26:5"},"She will be a place for the spreading of nets in the middle of the sea; for I have spoken it,’ says the Lord ALLAH. ‘She\nwill become plunder for the nations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 26:6"},"Her daughters who are in the field will be slain with the sword. Then they will know that I am the LORD.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 26:7"},"“For the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I will bring on Tyre Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, king of kings, from the north,\nwith horses, with chariots, with horsemen, and an army with many people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 26:8"},"He will kill your daughters in the field with the sword. He will make forts against you, cast up a mound against you, and\nraise up the buckler against you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 26:9"},"He will set his battering engines against your walls, and with his axes he will break down your towers.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 26:10"},"By reason of the abundance of his horses, their dust will cover you. Your walls will shake at the noise of the horsemen,\nof the wagons, and of the chariots, when he enters into your gates, as men enter into a city which is broken open.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 26:11"},"He will tread down all your streets with the hoofs of his horses. He will kill your people with the sword. The pillars of\nyour strength will go down to the ground. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 26:12"},"They will make a plunder of your riches, and make a prey of your merchandise. They will break down your walls, and\ndestroy your pleasant houses. They will lay your stones, your timber, and your dust in the middle of the waters.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 26:13"},"I will cause the noise of your songs to cease. The sound of your harps won’t be heard any more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 26:14"},"I will make you a bare rock. You will be a place for the spreading of nets. You will be built no more; for I the LORD\nhave spoken it,’ says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 26:15"},"“The Lord ALLAH says to Tyre: ‘Won’t the islands shake at the sound of your fall, when the wounded groan, when the\nslaughter is made within you? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 26:16"},"Then all the princes of the sea will come down from their thrones, and lay aside their robes, and strip off their\nembroidered garments. They will clothe themselves with trembling. They will sit on the ground, and will tremble every moment,\nand be astonished at you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 26:17"},"They will take up a lamentation over you, and tell you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“How you are destroyed, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who were inhabited by seafaring men, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the renowned city, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who was strong in the sea, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["she and her inhabitants, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["who caused their terror to be on all who lived there!” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 26:18"},"Now the islands will tremble in the day of your fall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Yes, the islands that are in the sea will be dismayed at your departure.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 26:19"},"“For the Lord ALLAH says: ‘When I make you a desolate city, like the cities that are not inhabited; when I bring up the\ndeep on you, and the great waters cover you; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 26:20"},"then I will bring you down with those who descend into the pit, to the people of old time, and will make you dwell in the\nlower parts of the earth, in the places that are desolate of old, with those who go down to the pit, that you be not inhabited;\nand I will set glory in the land of the living. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 26:21"},"I will make you a terror, and you will no more have any being. Though you are sought for, yet you will never be found\nagain,’ says the Lord ALLAH.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"27","sid":"EZK 27"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 27:1"},"The LORD’s word came again to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 27:2"},"“You, son of man, take up a lamentation over Tyre; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 27:3"},"and tell Tyre, ‘You who dwell at the entry of the sea, who are the merchant of the peoples to many islands, the Lord ALLAH\nsays: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You, Tyre, have said, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["‘I am perfect in beauty.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 27:4"},"Your borders are in the heart of the seas. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your builders have perfected your beauty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 27:5"},"They have made all your planks of cypress trees from Senir.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have taken a cedar from Lebanon to make a mast for you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 27:6"},"They have made your oars of the oaks of Bashan. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have made your benches of ivory inlaid in cypress wood from the islands of Kittim.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 27:7"},"Your sail was of fine linen with embroidered work from Egypt,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that it might be to you for a banner. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Blue and purple from the islands of Elishah was your awning.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 27:8"},"The inhabitants of Sidon and Arvad were your rowers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Your wise men, Tyre, were in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They were your pilots. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 27:9"},"The old men of Gebal \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its wise men were your repairers of ship seams in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["All the ships of the sea with their mariners were in you \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["to deal in your merchandise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 27:10"},"“‘“Persia, Lud, and Put were in your army, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your men of war. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They hung the shield and helmet in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They showed your beauty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 27:11"},"The men of Arvad with your army were on your walls all around,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and valiant men were in your towers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They hung their shields on your walls all around. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They have perfected your beauty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 27:12"},"“‘“Tarshish was your merchant by reason of the multitude of all kinds of riches. They traded for your wares with silver,\niron, tin, and lead. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 27:13"},"“‘“Javan, Tubal, and Meshech were your traders. They traded the persons of men and vessels of bronze for your\nmerchandise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 27:14"},"“‘“They of the house of Togarmah traded for your wares with horses, war horses, and mules.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 27:15"},"“‘“The men of Dedan traded with you. Many islands were the market of your hand. They brought you horns of ivory and ebony\nin exchange. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 27:16"},"“‘“Syria was your merchant by reason of the multitude of your handiworks. They traded for your wares with emeralds,\npurple, embroidered work, fine linen, coral, and rubies. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 27:17"},"“‘“Judah and the land of Israel were your traders. They traded wheat of Minnith, confections, honey, oil, and balm for\nyour merchandise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 27:18"},"“‘“Damascus was your merchant for the multitude of your handiworks, by reason of the multitude of all kinds of riches,\nwith the wine of Helbon, and white wool. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 27:19"},"“‘“Vedan and Javan traded with yarn for your wares: bright iron, cassia, and calamus were amongst your merchandise.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 27:20"},"“‘“Dedan was your trafficker in precious cloths for riding.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 27:21"},"“‘“Arabia, and all the princes of Kedar were the merchants of your hand; in lambs, rams, and goats. In these, they were\nyour merchants. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 27:22"},"“‘“The traders of Sheba and Raamah were your traders. They traded for your wares with the chief of all spices, and with\nall precious stones, and gold. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 27:23"},"“‘“Haran, Canneh, and Eden, the traders of Sheba, Asshur and Chilmad, were your traders.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 27:24"},"These were your traders in choice wares, in wrappings of blue and embroidered work, and in chests of rich clothing, bound\nwith cords and made of cedar, amongst your merchandise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 27:25"},"“‘“The ships of Tarshish were your caravans for your merchandise.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You were replenished \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and made very glorious in the heart of the seas. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 27:26"},"Your rowers have brought you into great waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The east wind has broken you in the heart of the seas. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 27:27"},"Your riches, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your wares, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your merchandise, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["your mariners, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your pilots, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["your repairers of ship seams, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["the dealers in your merchandise, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all your men of war, who are in you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["with all your company which is amongst you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will fall into the heart of the seas in the day of your ruin.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 27:28"},"At the sound of the cry of your pilots, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the pasture lands will shake. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 27:29"},"All who handle the oars, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the mariners and all the pilots of the sea, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["will come down from their ships. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will stand on the land, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 27:30"},"and will cause their voice to be heard over you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will cry bitterly. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will cast up dust on their heads. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will wallow in the ashes. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 27:31"},"They will make themselves bald for you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and clothe themselves with sackcloth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will weep for you in bitterness of soul, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with bitter mourning. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 27:32"},"In their wailing they will take up a lamentation for you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and lament over you, saying, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Who is there like Tyre, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["like her who is brought to silence in the middle of the sea?’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 27:33"},"When your wares went out of the seas, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you filled many peoples. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You enriched the kings of the earth \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the multitude of your riches and of your merchandise. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 27:34"},"In the time that you were broken by the seas, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the depths of the waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["your merchandise \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all your company fell within you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 27:35"},"All the inhabitants of the islands are astonished at you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their kings are horribly afraid. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are troubled in their face. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"EZK 27:36"},"The merchants amongst the peoples hiss at you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have become a terror, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you will be no more.”’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"28","sid":"EZK 28"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 28:1"},"The LORD’s word came again to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 28:2"},"“Son of man, tell the prince of Tyre, ‘The Lord ALLAH says:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Because your heart is lifted up, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you have said, ‘I am a god, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I sit in the seat of Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the middle of the seas;’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["yet you are man, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and not Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["though you set your heart as the heart of Allah— \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 28:3"},"behold, you are wiser than Daniel; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["there is no secret that is hidden from you; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 28:4"},"by your wisdom and by your understanding you have gotten yourself riches,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and have gotten gold and silver into your treasures; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 28:5"},"by your great wisdom \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and by your trading you have increased your riches, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and your heart is lifted up because of your riches—” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 28:6"},"“‘therefore the Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Because you have set your heart as the heart of Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 28:7"},"therefore, behold, I will bring strangers on you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the terrible of the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will draw their swords against the beauty of your wisdom.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will defile your brightness. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 28:8"},"They will bring you down to the pit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You will die the death of those who are slain \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the heart of the seas. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 28:9"},"Will you yet say before him who kills you, ‘I am Allah’? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["But you are man, and not Allah, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the hand of him who wounds you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 28:10"},"You will die the death of the uncircumcised \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the hand of strangers; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for I have spoken it,” says the Lord ALLAH.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 28:11"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 28:12"},"“Son of man, take up a lamentation over the king of Tyre, and tell him, ‘The Lord ALLAH says:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You were the seal of full measure, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["full of wisdom, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and perfect in beauty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 28:13"},"You were in Eden, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the garden of Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Every precious stone adorned you: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["ruby, topaz, emerald, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["chrysolite, onyx, jasper, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["sapphire,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["28:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["or, lapis lazuli "]}],"caller":"+"}," turquoise, and beryl.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Gold work of tambourines \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and of pipes was in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They were prepared in the day that you were created. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 28:14"},"You were the anointed cherub who covers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then I set you up on the holy mountain of Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have walked up and down in the middle of the stones of fire.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 28:15"},"You were perfect in your ways from the day that you were created,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["until unrighteousness was found in you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 28:16"},"By the abundance of your commerce, your insides were filled with violence,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you have sinned. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore I have cast you as profane out of Allah’s mountain.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have destroyed you, covering cherub, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["from the middle of the stones of fire. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 28:17"},"Your heart was lifted up because of your beauty. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have corrupted your wisdom by reason of your splendour. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have cast you to the ground. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I have laid you before kings, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that they may see you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 28:18"},"By the multitude of your iniquities, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the unrighteousness of your commerce, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you have profaned your sanctuaries. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Therefore I have brought out a fire from the middle of you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["It has devoured you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have turned you to ashes on the earth \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the sight of all those who see you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 28:19"},"All those who know you amongst the peoples will be astonished at you.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You have become a terror, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and you will exist no more.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 28:20"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 28:21"},"“Son of man, set your face towards Sidon, and prophesy against it,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 28:22"},"and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I am against you, Sidon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will be glorified amongst you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Then they will know that I am the LORD, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I have executed judgements in her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and am sanctified in her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 28:23"},"For I will send pestilence into her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and blood into her streets. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The wounded will fall within her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with the sword on her on every side. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then they will know that I am the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 28:24"},"“‘“There will be no more a pricking brier to the house of Israel, nor a hurting thorn of any that are around them that\nscorned them. Then they will know that I am the Lord ALLAH.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 28:25"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “When I have gathered the house of Israel from the peoples amongst whom they are scattered, and am\nsanctified in them in the sight of the nations, then they will dwell in their own land which I gave to my servant Yaqub.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 28:26"},"They will dwell in it securely. Yes, they will build houses, plant vineyards, and will dwell securely, when I have\nexecuted judgements on all those who scorn them all around. Then they will know that I am the LORD their Allah.”’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"29","sid":"EZK 29"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 29:1"},"In the tenth year, in the tenth month, on the twelfth day of the month, the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 29:2"},"“Son of man, set your face against Pharaoh king of Egypt, and prophesy against him and against all Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 29:3"},"Speak and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Behold, I am against you, Pharaoh king of Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the great monster that lies in the middle of his rivers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["that has said, ‘My river is my own, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I have made it for myself.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 29:4"},"I will put hooks in your jaws, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will make the fish of your rivers stick to your scales.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will bring you up out of the middle of your rivers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with all the fish of your rivers which stick to your scales.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 29:5"},"I’ll cast you out into the wilderness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["you and all the fish of your rivers. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You’ll fall on the open field. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["You won’t be brought together or gathered. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I have given you for food to the animals of the earth \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and to the birds of the sky. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 29:6"},"“‘“All the inhabitants of Egypt will know that I am the LORD, because they have been a staff of reed to the house of\nIsrael. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 29:7"},"When they took hold of you by your hand, you broke, and tore all their shoulders. When they leaned on you, you broke, and\nparalysed all of their thighs.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 29:8"},"“‘Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I will bring a sword on you, and will cut off man and animal from you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 29:9"},"The land of Egypt will be a desolation and a waste. Then they will know that I am the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“‘“Because he has said, ‘The river is mine, and I have made it;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 29:10"},"therefore, behold, I am against you, and against your rivers. I will make the land of Egypt an utter waste and\ndesolation, from the tower of Seveneh even to the border of Ethiopia.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 29:11"},"No foot of man will pass through it, nor will any animal foot pass through it. It won’t be inhabited for forty years.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 29:12"},"I will make the land of Egypt a desolation in the middle of the countries that are desolate. Her cities amongst the\ncities that are laid waste will be a desolation forty years. I will scatter the Egyptians amongst the nations, and will\ndisperse them through the countries.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 29:13"},"“‘For the Lord ALLAH says: “At the end of forty years I will gather the Egyptians from the peoples where they were\nscattered. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 29:14"},"I will reverse the captivity of Egypt, and will cause them to return into the land of Pathros, into the land of their\nbirth. They will be a lowly kingdom, there. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 29:15"},"It will be the lowest of the kingdoms. It won’t lift itself up above the nations any more. I will diminish them, so that\nthey will no longer rule over the nations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 29:16"},"It will no longer be the confidence of the house of Israel, bringing iniquity to memory, when they turn to look after\nthem. Then they will know that I am the Lord ALLAH.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 29:17"},"It came to pass in the twenty-seventh year, in the first month, in the first day of the month, the LORD’s word came to\nme, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 29:18"},"“Son of man, Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon caused his army to serve a great service against Tyre. Every head was made\nbald, and every shoulder was worn; yet he had no wages, nor did his army, from Tyre, for the service that he had served against\nit. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 29:19"},"Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I will give the land of Egypt to Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon. He will carry\noff her multitude, take her plunder, and take her prey. That will be the wages for his army.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 29:20"},"I have given him the land of Egypt as his payment for which he served, because they worked for me,’ says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 29:21"},"“In that day I will cause a horn to sprout for the house of Israel, and I will open your mouth amongst them. Then they\nwill know that I am the LORD.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"30","sid":"EZK 30"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 30:1"},"The LORD’s word came again to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 30:2"},"“Son of man, prophesy, and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“Wail, ‘Alas for the day!’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 30:3"},"For the day is near, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even the LORD’s day is near. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["It will be a day of clouds, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a time of the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 30:4"},"A sword will come on Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and anguish will be in Ethiopia, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when the slain fall in Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They take away her multitude, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her foundations are broken down. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 30:5"},"“‘“Ethiopia, Put, Lud, all the mixed people, Cub, and the children of the land that is allied with them, will fall with\nthem by the sword.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 30:6"},"“‘The LORD says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“They also who uphold Egypt will fall. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The pride of her power will come down. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will fall by the sword in it from the tower of Seveneh,”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 30:7"},"“They will be desolate in the middle of the countries that are desolate.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Her cities will be amongst the cities that are wasted. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 30:8"},"They will know that I am the LORD \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I have set a fire in Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all her helpers are destroyed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 30:9"},"“‘“In that day messengers will go out from before me in ships to make the careless Ethiopians afraid. There will be\nanguish on them, as in the day of Egypt; for, behold, it comes.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 30:10"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will also make the multitude of Egypt to cease, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the hand of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 30:11"},"He and his people with him, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the terrible of the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["will be brought in to destroy the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will draw their swords against Egypt, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fill the land with the slain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 30:12"},"I will make the rivers dry, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will sell the land into the hand of evil men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will make the land desolate, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all that is therein, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["by the hand of strangers: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I, the LORD, have spoken it.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 30:13"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“I will also destroy the idols, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and I will cause the images to cease from Memphis. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["There will be no more a prince from the land of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will put a fear in the land of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 30:14"},"I will make Pathros desolate, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will set a fire in Zoan, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and will execute judgements on No. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 30:15"},"I will pour my wrath on Sin, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["the stronghold of Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will cut off the multitude of No. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 30:16"},"I will set a fire in Egypt \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Sin will be in great anguish. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["No will be broken up. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Memphis will have adversaries in the daytime. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 30:17"},"The young men of Aven and of Pibeseth will fall by the sword.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will go into captivity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 30:18"},"At Tehaphnehes also the day will withdraw itself, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I break the yokes of Egypt, there. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The pride of her power will cease in her. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["As for her, a cloud will cover her, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and her daughters will go into captivity. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 30:19"},"Thus I will execute judgements on Egypt. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Then they will know that I am the LORD.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 30:20"},"In the eleventh year, in the first month, in the seventh day of the month, the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 30:21"},"“Son of man, I have broken the arm of Pharaoh king of Egypt. Behold, it has not been bound up, to apply medicines, to put\na bandage to bind it, that it become strong to hold the sword. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 30:22"},"Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I am against Pharaoh king of Egypt, and will break his arms, the strong arm, and\nthat which was broken. I will cause the sword to fall out of his hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 30:23"},"I will scatter the Egyptians amongst the nations, and will disperse them through the countries.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 30:24"},"I will strengthen the arms of the king of Babylon, and put my sword in his hand; but I will break the arms of Pharaoh,\nand he will groan before the king of Babylon with the groaning of a mortally wounded man.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 30:25"},"I will hold up the arms of the king of Babylon; and the arms of Pharaoh will fall down. Then they will know that I am the\nLORD, when I put my sword into the hand of the king of Babylon, and he stretches it out on the land of Egypt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 30:26"},"I will scatter the Egyptians amongst the nations, and disperse them through the countries. Then they will know that I am\nthe LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"31","sid":"EZK 31"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 31:1"},"In the eleventh year, in the third month, in the first day of the month, The LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 31:2"},"“Son of man, tell Pharaoh king of Egypt, and his multitude:\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["‘Whom are you like in your greatness? \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 31:3"},"Behold, the Assyrian was a cedar in Lebanon \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["with beautiful branches, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and with a forest-like shade, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["of high stature; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its top was amongst the thick boughs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 31:4"},"The waters nourished it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The deep made it to grow. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Its rivers ran all around its plantation; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and it sent out its channels to all the trees of the field. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 31:5"},"Therefore its stature was exalted above all the trees of the field;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and its boughs were multiplied. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["Its branches became long by reason of many waters, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when it spread them out. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 31:6"},"All the birds of the sky made their nests in its boughs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["Under its branches, all the animals of the field gave birth to their young.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["All great nations lived under its shadow. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 31:7"},"Thus was it beautiful in its greatness, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the length of its branches; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["for its root was by many waters. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 31:8"},"The cedars in the garden of Allah could not hide it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The cypress trees were not like its boughs. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["The pine trees were not as its branches; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor was any tree in the garden of Allah like it in its beauty.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 31:9"},"I made it beautiful by the multitude of its branches, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["so that all the trees of Eden, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["that were in the garden of Allah, envied it.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 31:10"},"“Therefore thus said the Lord ALLAH: ‘Because you are exalted in stature, and he has set his top amongst the thick\nboughs, and his heart is lifted up in his height; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 31:11"},"I will even deliver him into the hand of the mighty one of the nations. He will surely deal with him. I have driven him\nout for his wickedness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 31:12"},"Strangers, the tyrants of the nations, have cut him off, and have left him. His branches have fallen on the mountains and\nin all the valleys and his boughs are broken by all the watercourses of the land. All the peoples of the earth have gone down\nfrom his shadow, and have left him. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 31:13"},"All the birds of the sky will dwell on his ruin, and all the animals of the field will be on his branches;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 31:14"},"to the end that none of all the trees by the waters exalt themselves in their stature, and don’t set their top amongst\nthe thick boughs. Their mighty ones don’t stand up on their height, even all who drink water; for they are all delivered to\ndeath, to the lower parts of the earth, amongst the children of men, with those who go down to the pit.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 31:15"},"“The Lord ALLAH says: ‘In the day when he went down to Sheol\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:15 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}],"caller":"+"}," I caused a mourning. I covered the deep for him, and I restrained its\nrivers. The great waters were stopped. I caused Lebanon to mourn for him, and all the trees of the field fainted for him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 31:16"},"I made the nations to shake at the sound of his fall, when I cast him down to\nSheol",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["31:16 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}],"caller":"+"}," with those who descend into the pit. All the trees of Eden, the\nchoice and best of Lebanon, all that drink water, were comforted in the lower parts of the earth.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 31:17"},"They also went down into Sheol with him to those who are slain by the sword; yes, those who were his arm, who lived under\nhis shadow in the middle of the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 31:18"},"“‘To whom are you thus like in glory and in greatness amongst the trees of Eden? Yet you will be brought down with the\ntrees of Eden to the lower parts of the earth. You will lie in the middle of the uncircumcised, with those who are slain by the\nsword. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“‘This is Pharaoh and all his multitude,’ says the Lord ALLAH.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"32","sid":"EZK 32"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 32:1"},"In the twelfth year, in the twelfth month, in the first day of the month, “the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 32:2"},"‘Son of man, take up a lamentation over Pharaoh king of Egypt, and tell him,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["“You were likened to a young lion of the nations; \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["yet you are as a monster in the seas. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["You broke out with your rivers, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and troubled the waters with your feet, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fouled their rivers.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 32:3"},"The Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“I will spread out my net on you with a company of many peoples;\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and they will bring you up in my net. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 32:4"},"I will leave you on the land. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will cast you out on the open field, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["and will cause all the birds of the sky to settle on you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["I will satisfy the animals of the whole earth with you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 32:5"},"I will lay your flesh on the mountains, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and fill the valleys with your height. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 32:6"},"I will also water the land in which you swim with your blood,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["even to the mountains. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The watercourses will be full of you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 32:7"},"When I extinguish you, I will cover the heavens \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and make its stars dark. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["I will cover the sun with a cloud, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and the moon won’t give its light. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 32:8"},"I will make all the bright lights of the sky dark over you,\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and set darkness on your land,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 32:9"},"“I will also trouble the hearts of many peoples, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["when I bring your destruction amongst the nations, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["into the countries which you have not known. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 32:10"},"Yes, I will make many peoples amazed at you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and their kings will be horribly afraid for you, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I brandish my sword before them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They will tremble at every moment, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["every man for his own life, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["in the day of your fall.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 32:11"},"For the Lord ALLAH says: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["“The sword of the king of Babylon will come on you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 32:12"},"I will cause your multitude to fall by the swords of the mighty.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["They are all the ruthless of the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["They will bring the pride of Egypt to nothing, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and all its multitude will be destroyed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 32:13"},"I will destroy also all its animals from beside many waters.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["The foot of man won’t trouble them any more, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["nor will the hoofs of animals trouble them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 32:14"},"Then I will make their waters clear, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["and cause their rivers to run like oil,” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 32:15"},"“When I make the land of Egypt desolate and waste, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["a land destitute of that of which it was full, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q1","content":["when I strike all those who dwell therein, \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"q2","content":["then they will know that I am the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 32:16"},"“‘“This is the lamentation with which they will lament. The daughters of the nations will lament with this. They will\nlament with it over Egypt, and over all her multitude,” says the Lord ALLAH.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 32:17"},"Also in the twelfth year, in the fifteenth day of the month, the LORD’s word came to me, saying,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 32:18"},"“Son of man, wail for the multitude of Egypt, and cast them down, even her and the daughters of the famous nations, to\nthe lower parts of the earth, with those who go down into the pit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 32:19"},"Whom do you pass in beauty? Go down, and be laid with the uncircumcised.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 32:20"},"They will fall amongst those who are slain by the sword. She is delivered to the sword. Draw her away with all her\nmultitudes. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 32:21"},"The strong amongst the mighty will speak to him out of the middle of Sheol\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["32:21 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}],"caller":"+"}," with those who help him. They have gone down. The uncircumcised lie\nstill, slain by the sword. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 32:22"},"“Asshur is there with all her company. Her graves are all around her. All of them slain, fallen by the sword;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 32:23"},"whose graves are set in the uttermost parts of the pit, and her company is around her grave; all of them slain, fallen by\nthe sword, who caused terror in the land of the living. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 32:24"},"“There is Elam and all her multitude around her grave; all of them slain, fallen by the sword, who have gone down\nuncircumcised into the lower parts of the earth, who caused their terror in the land of the living, and have borne their shame\nwith those who go down to the pit. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 32:25"},"They have set her a bed amongst the slain with all her multitude. Her graves are around her; all of them uncircumcised,\nslain by the sword; for their terror was caused in the land of the living, and they have borne their shame with those who go\ndown to the pit. He is put amongst those who are slain. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 32:26"},"“There is Meshech, Tubal, and all their multitude. Their graves are around them, all of them uncircumcised, slain by the\nsword; for they caused their terror in the land of the living. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 32:27"},"They will not lie with the mighty who are fallen of the uncircumcised, who have gone down to Sheol with their weapons of\nwar, and have laid their swords under their heads, and their iniquities are on their bones; for they were the terror of the\nmighty in the land of the living. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 32:28"},"“But you will be broken amongst the uncircumcised, and will lie with those who are slain by the sword.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 32:29"},"“There is Edom, her kings, and all her princes, who in their might are laid with those who are slain by the sword. They\nwill lie with the uncircumcised, and with those who go down to the pit.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 32:30"},"“There are the princes of the north, all of them, and all the Sidonians, who have gone down with the slain. They are put\nto shame in the terror which they caused by their might. They lie uncircumcised with those who are slain by the sword, and bear\ntheir shame with those who go down to the pit. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 32:31"},"“Pharaoh will see them, and will be comforted over all his multitude, even Pharaoh and all his army, slain by the sword,”\nsays the Lord ALLAH. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 32:32"},"“For I have put his terror in the land of the living. He will be laid amongst the uncircumcised, with those who are slain\nby the sword, even Pharaoh and all his multitude,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"33","sid":"EZK 33"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 33:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 33:2"},"“Son of man, speak to the children of your people, and tell them, ‘When I bring the sword on a land, and the people of the\nland take a man from amongst them, and set him for their watchman;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 33:3"},"if, when he sees the sword come on the land, he blows the trumpet, and warns the people;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 33:4"},"then whoever hears the sound of the trumpet, and doesn’t heed the warning, if the sword comes, and takes him away, his\nblood will be on his own head. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 33:5"},"He heard the sound of the trumpet, and didn’t take warning. His blood will be on him; whereas if he had heeded the\nwarning, he would have delivered his soul. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 33:6"},"But if the watchman sees the sword come, and doesn’t blow the trumpet, and the people aren’t warned, and the sword comes,\nand takes any person from amongst them; he is taken away in his iniquity, but his blood I will require at the watchman’s hand.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 33:7"},"“So you, son of man: I have set you a watchman to the house of Israel. Therefore hear the word from my mouth, and give\nthem warnings from me. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 33:8"},"When I tell the wicked, ‘O wicked man, you will surely die,’ and you don’t speak to warn the wicked from his way; that\nwicked man will die in his iniquity, but I will require his blood at your hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 33:9"},"Nevertheless, if you warn the wicked of his way to turn from it, and he doesn’t turn from his way; he will die in his\niniquity, but you have delivered your soul. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 33:10"},"“You, son of man, tell the house of Israel: ‘You say this, “Our transgressions and our sins are on us, and we pine away\nin them. How then can we live?”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 33:11"},"Tell them, ‘“As I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “I have no pleasure in the death of the wicked; but that the wicked turn\nfrom his way and live. Turn, turn from your evil ways! For why will you die, house of Israel?”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 33:12"},"“You, son of man, tell the children of your people, ‘The righteousness of the righteous will not deliver him in the day\nof his disobedience. And as for the wickedness of the wicked, he will not fall by it in the day that he turns from his\nwickedness; neither will he who is righteous be able to live by it in the day that he sins.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 33:13"},"When I tell the righteous that he will surely live; if he trusts in his righteousness, and commits iniquity, none of his\nrighteous deeds will be remembered; but he will die in his iniquity that he has committed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 33:14"},"Again, when I say to the wicked, “You will surely die;” if he turns from his sin, and does that which is lawful and\nright; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 33:15"},"if the wicked restore the pledge, give again that which he had taken by robbery, walk in the statutes of life, committing\nno iniquity; he will surely live. He will not die. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 33:16"},"None of his sins that he has committed will be remembered against him. He has done that which is lawful and right. He\nwill surely live. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 33:17"},"“‘Yet the children of your people say, “The way of the Lord is not fair;” but as for them, their way is not fair.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 33:18"},"When the righteous turns from his righteousness, and commits iniquity, he will even die therein.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 33:19"},"When the wicked turns from his wickedness, and does that which is lawful and right, he will live by it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 33:20"},"Yet you say, “The way of the Lord is not fair.” House of Israel, I will judge every one of you after his ways.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 33:21"},"In the twelfth year of our captivity, in the tenth month, in the fifth day of the month, one who had escaped out of\nJerusalem came to me, saying, “The city has been defeated!” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 33:22"},"Now the LORD’s hand had been on me in the evening, before he who had escaped came; and he had opened my mouth, until he\ncame to me in the morning; and my mouth was opened, and I was no longer mute.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 33:23"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 33:24"},"“Son of man, those who inhabit the waste places in the land of Israel speak, saying, ‘Ibrahim was one, and he inherited\nthe land; but we are many. The land is given us for inheritance.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 33:25"},"Therefore tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “You eat with the blood, and lift up your eyes to your idols, and shed blood.\nSo should you possess the land? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 33:26"},"You stand on your sword, you work abomination, and every one of you defiles his neighbour’s wife. So should you possess\nthe land?”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 33:27"},"“You shall tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “As I live, surely those who are in the waste places will fall by the sword.\nI will give he who is in the open field to the animals to be devoured; and those who are in the strongholds and in the caves\nwill die of the pestilence. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 33:28"},"I will make the land a desolation and an astonishment. The pride of her power will cease. The mountains of Israel will be\ndesolate, so that no one will pass through. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 33:29"},"Then they will know that I am the LORD, when I have made the land a desolation and an astonishment, because of all their\nabominations which they have committed.”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 33:30"},"“As for you, son of man, the children of your people talk about you by the walls and in the doors of the houses, and\nspeak to one another, everyone to his brother, saying, ‘Please come and hear what the word is that comes out from the LORD.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 33:31"},"They come to you as the people come, and they sit before you as my people, and they hear your words, but don’t do them;\nfor with their mouth they show much love, but their heart goes after their gain.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 33:32"},"Behold, you are to them as a very lovely song of one who has a pleasant voice, and can play well on an instrument; for\nthey hear your words, but they don’t do them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 33:33"},"“When this comes to pass—behold, it comes—then they will know that a prophet has been amongst them.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"34","sid":"EZK 34"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 34:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 34:2"},"“Son of man, prophesy against the shepherds of Israel. Prophesy, and tell them, even the shepherds, ‘The Lord ALLAH says:\n“Woe to the shepherds of Israel who feed themselves! Shouldn’t the shepherds feed the sheep?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 34:3"},"You eat the fat. You clothe yourself with the wool. You kill the fatlings, but you don’t feed the sheep.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 34:4"},"You haven’t strengthened the diseased. You haven’t healed that which was sick. You haven’t bound up that which was broken.\nYou haven’t brought back that which was driven away. You haven’t sought that which was lost, but you have ruled over them with\nforce and with rigor. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 34:5"},"They were scattered, because there was no shepherd. They became food to all the animals of the field, and were scattered.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 34:6"},"My sheep wandered through all the mountains, and on every high hill. Yes, my sheep were scattered on all the surface of\nthe earth. There was no one who searched or sought.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 34:7"},"“‘Therefore, you shepherds, hear the LORD’s word: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 34:8"},"“As I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “surely because my sheep became a prey, and my sheep became food to all the animals of\nthe field, because there was no shepherd. My shepherds didn’t search for my sheep, but the shepherds fed themselves, and didn’t\nfeed my sheep.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 34:9"},"Therefore, you shepherds, hear the LORD’s word: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 34:10"},"The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I am against the shepherds. I will require my sheep at their hand, and cause them to cease\nfrom feeding the sheep. The shepherds won’t feed themselves any more. I will deliver my sheep from their mouth, that they may\nnot be food for them.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 34:11"},"“‘For the Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I myself, even I, will search for my sheep, and will seek them out.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 34:12"},"As a shepherd seeks out his flock in the day that he is amongst his sheep that are scattered abroad, so I will seek out\nmy sheep. I will deliver them out of all places where they have been scattered in the cloudy and dark day.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 34:13"},"I will bring them out from the peoples, and gather them from the countries, and will bring them into their own land. I\nwill feed them on the mountains of Israel, by the watercourses, and in all the inhabited places of the country.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 34:14"},"I will feed them with good pasture; and their fold will be on the mountains of the height of Israel. There they will lie\ndown in a good fold. They will feed on fat pasture on the mountains of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 34:15"},"I myself will be the shepherd of my sheep, and I will cause them to lie down,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 34:16"},"“I will seek that which was lost, and will bring back that which was driven away, and will bind up that which was broken,\nand will strengthen that which was sick; but I will destroy the fat and the strong. I will feed them in justice.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 34:17"},"“As for you, O my flock, the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Behold, I judge between sheep and sheep, the rams and the male goats.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 34:18"},"Does it seem a small thing to you to have fed on the good pasture, but you must tread down with your feet the residue of\nyour pasture? And to have drunk of the clear waters, but must you foul the residue with your feet?\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 34:19"},"As for my sheep, they eat that which you have trodden with your feet, and they drink that which you have fouled with your\nfeet.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 34:20"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says to them: ‘Behold, I, even I, will judge between the fat sheep and the lean sheep.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 34:21"},"Because you thrust with side and with shoulder, and push all the diseased with your horns, until you have scattered them\nabroad; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 34:22"},"therefore I will save my flock, and they will no more be a prey. I will judge between sheep and sheep.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 34:23"},"I will set up one shepherd over them, and he will feed them, even my servant Dawood. He will feed them, and he will be\ntheir shepherd. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 34:24"},"I, the LORD, will be their Allah, and my servant Dawood prince amongst them. I, the LORD, have spoken it.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 34:25"},"“‘I will make with them a covenant of peace, and will cause evil animals to cease out of the land. They will dwell\nsecurely in the wilderness, and sleep in the woods. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 34:26"},"I will make them and the places around my hill a blessing. I will cause the shower to come down in its season. There will\nbe showers of blessing. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 34:27"},"The tree of the field will yield its fruit, and the earth will yield its increase, and they will be secure in their land.\nThen they will know that I am the LORD, when I have broken the bars of their yoke, and have delivered them out of the hand of\nthose who made slaves of them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 34:28"},"They will no more be a prey to the nations, neither will the animals of the earth devour them; but they will dwell\nsecurely, and no one will make them afraid. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 34:29"},"I will raise up to them a plantation for renown, and they will no more be consumed with famine in the land, and not bear\nthe shame of the nations any more. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 34:30"},"They will know that I, the LORD, their Allah am with them, and that they, the house of Israel, are my people, says the\nLord ALLAH. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 34:31"},"You my sheep, the sheep of my pasture, are men, and I am your Allah,’ says the Lord ALLAH.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"35","sid":"EZK 35"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 35:1"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 35:2"},"“Son of man, set your face against Mount Seir, and prophesy against it,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 35:3"},"and tell it, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I am against you, Mount Seir, and I will stretch out my hand against you. I\nwill make you a desolation and an astonishment. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 35:4"},"I will lay your cities waste, and you will be desolate. Then you will know that I am the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 35:5"},"“‘“Because you have had a perpetual hostility, and have given over the children of Israel to the power of the sword in the\ntime of their calamity, in the time of the iniquity of the end; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 35:6"},"therefore, as I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “I will prepare you for blood, and blood will pursue you. Since you have not\nhated blood, therefore blood will pursue you. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 35:7"},"Thus I will make Mount Seir an astonishment and a desolation. I will cut off from it him who passes through and him who\nreturns. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 35:8"},"I will fill its mountains with its slain. The slain with the sword will fall in your hills and in your valleys and in all\nyour watercourses. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 35:9"},"I will make you a perpetual desolation, and your cities will not be inhabited. Then you will know that I am the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 35:10"},"“‘“Because you have said, ‘These two nations and these two countries will be mine, and we will possess it;’ whereas the\nLORD was there: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 35:11"},"therefore, as I live,” says the Lord ALLAH, “I will do according to your anger, and according to your envy which you have\nshown out of your hatred against them; and I will make myself known amongst them when I judge you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 35:12"},"You will know that I, the LORD, have heard all your insults which you have spoken against the mountains of Israel,\nsaying, ‘They have been laid desolate. They have been given us to devour.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 35:13"},"You have magnified yourselves against me with your mouth, and have multiplied your words against me. I have heard it.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 35:14"},"The Lord ALLAH says: “When the whole earth rejoices, I will make you desolate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 35:15"},"As you rejoiced over the inheritance of the house of Israel because it was desolate, so I will do to you. You will be\ndesolate, Mount Seir, and all Edom, even all of it. Then they will know that I am the LORD.’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"36","sid":"EZK 36"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 36:1"},"You, son of man, prophesy to the mountains of Israel, and say, “You mountains of Israel, hear the LORD’s word.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 36:2"},"The Lord ALLAH says: ‘Because the enemy has said against you, “Aha!” and, “The ancient high places are ours in\npossession!”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 36:3"},"therefore prophesy, and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Because, even because they have made you desolate, and swallowed you\nup on every side, that you might be a possession to the residue of the nations, and you are taken up in the lips of talkers,\nand the evil report of the people;” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 36:4"},"therefore, you mountains of Israel, hear the word of the Lord ALLAH: The Lord ALLAH says to the mountains and to the\nhills, to the watercourses and to the valleys, to the desolate wastes and to the cities that are forsaken, which have become a\nprey and derision to the residue of the nations that are all around;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 36:5"},"therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “Surely in the fire of my jealousy I have spoken against the residue of the nations, and\nagainst all Edom, that have appointed my land to themselves for a possession with the joy of all their heart, with despite of\nsoul, to cast it out for a prey.”’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 36:6"},"Therefore prophesy concerning the land of Israel, and tell the mountains, the hills, the watercourses and the valleys,\n‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I have spoken in my jealousy and in my wrath, because you have borne the shame of the nations.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 36:7"},"Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: “I have sworn, ‘Surely the nations that are around you will bear their shame.’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 36:8"},"“‘“But you, mountains of Israel, you shall shoot out your branches, and yield your fruit to my people Israel; for they are\nat hand to come. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 36:9"},"For, behold, I am for you, and I will come to you, and you will be tilled and sown.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 36:10"},"I will multiply men on you, all the house of Israel, even all of it. The cities will be inhabited, and the waste places\nwill be built. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 36:11"},"I will multiply man and animal on you. They will increase and be fruitful. I will cause you to be inhabited as you were\nbefore, and you will do better than at your beginnings. Then you will know that I am the LORD.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 36:12"},"Yes, I will cause men to walk on you, even my people Israel. They will possess you, and you will be their inheritance,\nand you will never again bereave them of their children.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 36:13"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Because they say to you, ‘You are a devourer of men, and have been a bereaver of your nation;’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 36:14"},"therefore you shall devour men no more, and not bereave your nation any more,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 36:15"},"“I won’t let you hear the shame of the nations any more. You won’t bear the reproach of the peoples any more, and you\nwon’t cause your nation to stumble any more,” says the Lord ALLAH.’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 36:16"},"Moreover the LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 36:17"},"“Son of man, when the house of Israel lived in their own land, they defiled it by their ways and by their deeds. Their\nway before me was as the uncleanness of a woman in her impurity.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 36:18"},"Therefore I poured out my wrath on them for the blood which they had poured out on the land, and because they had defiled\nit with their idols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 36:19"},"I scattered them amongst the nations, and they were dispersed through the countries. I judged them according to their way\nand according to their deeds. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 36:20"},"When they came to the nations where they went, they profaned my holy name; in that men said of them, ‘These are the\nLORD’s people, and have left his land.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 36:21"},"But I had respect for my holy name, which the house of Israel had profaned amongst the nations where they went.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 36:22"},"“Therefore tell the house of Israel, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “I don’t do this for your sake, house of Israel, but for my\nholy name, which you have profaned amongst the nations where you went.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 36:23"},"I will sanctify my great name, which has been profaned amongst the nations, which you have profaned amongst them. Then\nthe nations will know that I am the LORD,” says the Lord ALLAH, “when I am proven holy in you before their eyes.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 36:24"},"“‘“For I will take you from amongst the nations and gather you out of all the countries, and will bring you into your own\nland. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 36:25"},"I will sprinkle clean water on you, and you will be clean. I will cleanse you from all your filthiness, and from all your\nidols. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 36:26"},"I will also give you a new heart, and I will put a new spirit within you. I will take away the stony heart out of your\nflesh, and I will give you a heart of flesh. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 36:27"},"I will put my Spirit within you, and cause you to walk in my statutes. You will keep my ordinances and do them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 36:28"},"You will dwell in the land that I gave to your fathers. You will be my people, and I will be your Allah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 36:29"},"I will save you from all your uncleanness. I will call for the grain, and will multiply it, and lay no famine on you.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 36:30"},"I will multiply the fruit of the tree and the increase of the field, that you may receive no more the reproach of famine\namongst the nations. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 36:31"},"“‘“Then you will remember your evil ways, and your deeds that were not good; and you will loathe yourselves in your own\nsight for your iniquities and for your abominations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 36:32"},"I don’t do this for your sake,” says the Lord ALLAH. “Let it be known to you: be ashamed and confounded for your ways,\nhouse of Israel.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 36:33"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “In the day that I cleanse you from all your iniquities, I will cause the cities to be inhabited\nand the waste places will be built. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 36:34"},"The land that was desolate will be tilled instead of being a desolation in the sight of all who passed by.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 36:35"},"They will say, ‘This land that was desolate has become like the garden of Eden. The waste, desolate, and ruined cities\nare fortified and inhabited.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"EZK 36:36"},"Then the nations that are left around you will know that I, the LORD, have built the ruined places, and planted that\nwhich was desolate. I, the LORD, have spoken it, and I will do it.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"EZK 36:37"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “For this, moreover, I will be enquired of by the house of Israel, to do it for them: I will\nincrease them with men like a flock. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"EZK 36:38"},"As the flock for sacrifice, as the flock of Jerusalem in her appointed feasts, so the waste cities will be filled with\nflocks of men. Then they will know that I am the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"37","sid":"EZK 37"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 37:1"},"The LORD’s hand was on me, and he brought me out in the LORD’s Spirit, and set me down in the middle of the valley; and it\nwas full of bones. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 37:2"},"He caused me to pass by them all around: and behold, there were very many in the open valley; and behold, they were very\ndry. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 37:3"},"He said to me, “Son of man, can these bones live?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["I answered, “Lord ALLAH, you know.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 37:4"},"Again he said to me, “Prophesy over these bones, and tell them, ‘You dry bones, hear the LORD’s word.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 37:5"},"The Lord ALLAH says to these bones: “Behold, I will cause breath to enter into you, and you will live.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 37:6"},"I will lay sinews on you, and will bring up flesh on you, and cover you with skin, and put breath in you, and you will\nlive. Then you will know that I am the LORD.”’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 37:7"},"So I prophesied as I was commanded. As I prophesied, there was a noise, and behold, there was an earthquake. Then the\nbones came together, bone to its bone. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 37:8"},"I saw, and, behold, there were sinews on them, and flesh came up, and skin covered them above; but there was no breath in\nthem. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 37:9"},"Then he said to me, “Prophesy to the wind, prophesy, son of man, and tell the wind, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Come from the\nfour winds, breath, and breathe on these slain, that they may live.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 37:10"},"So I prophesied as he commanded me, and the breath came into them, and they lived, and stood up on their feet, an\nexceedingly great army. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 37:11"},"Then he said to me, “Son of man, these bones are the whole house of Israel. Behold, they say, ‘Our bones are dried up,\nand our hope is lost. We are completely cut off.’ \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 37:12"},"Therefore prophesy, and tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I will open your graves, and cause you to come up out\nof your graves, my people; and I will bring you into the land of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 37:13"},"You will know that I am the LORD, when I have opened your graves, and caused you to come up out of your graves, my\npeople. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 37:14"},"I will put my Spirit in you, and you will live. Then I will place you in your own land; and you will know that I, the\nLORD, have spoken it and performed it,” says the LORD.’” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"b"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 37:15"},"The LORD’s word came again to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 37:16"},"“You, son of man, take one stick, and write on it, ‘For Judah, and for the children of Israel his companions.’ Then take\nanother stick, and write on it, ‘For Yusuf, the stick of Ephraim, and for all the house of Israel his companions.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 37:17"},"Then join them for yourself to one another into one stick, that they may become one in your hand.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 37:18"},"“When the children of your people speak to you, saying, ‘Won’t you show us what you mean by these?’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 37:19"},"tell them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I will take the stick of Yusuf, which is in the hand of Ephraim, and the tribes\nof Israel his companions; and I will put them with it, with the stick of Judah, and make them one stick, and they will be one\nin my hand. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 37:20"},"The sticks on which you write will be in your hand before their eyes.”’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 37:21"},"Say to them, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I will take the children of Israel from amongst the nations, where they have\ngone, and will gather them on every side, and bring them into their own land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 37:22"},"I will make them one nation in the land, on the mountains of Israel. One king will be king to them all. They will no\nlonger be two nations. They won’t be divided into two kingdoms any more at all.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 37:23"},"They won’t defile themselves any more with their idols, nor with their detestable things, nor with any of their\ntransgressions; but I will save them out of all their dwelling places, in which they have sinned, and will cleanse them. So\nthey will be my people, and I will be their Allah. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 37:24"},"“‘“My servant Dawood will be king over them. They all will have one shepherd. They will also walk in my ordinances, and\nobserve my statutes, and do them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 37:25"},"They will dwell in the land that I have given to Yaqub my servant, in which your fathers lived. They will dwell therein,\nthey, and their children, and their children’s children, forever. Dawood my servant will be their prince forever.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 37:26"},"Moreover I will make a covenant of peace with them. It will be an everlasting covenant with them. I will place them,\nmultiply them, and will set my sanctuary amongst them forever more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 37:27"},"My tent also will be with them. I will be their Allah, and they will be my people.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 37:28"},"The nations will know that I am the LORD who sanctifies Israel, when my sanctuary is amongst them forever more.”’”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"38","sid":"EZK 38"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 38:1"},"The LORD’s word came to me, saying, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 38:2"},"“Son of man, set your face towards Gog, of the land of Magog, the prince of Rosh, Meshech, and Tubal, and prophesy against\nhim, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 38:3"},"and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I am against you, Gog, prince of Rosh, Meshech, and Tubal.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 38:4"},"I will turn you around, and put hooks into your jaws, and I will bring you out, with all your army, horses and horsemen,\nall of them clothed in full armour, a great company with buckler and shield, all of them handling swords;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 38:5"},"Persia, Cush, and Put with them, all of them with shield and helmet;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 38:6"},"Gomer, and all his hordes; the house of Togarmah in the uttermost parts of the north, and all his hordes; even many\npeoples with you. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 38:7"},"“‘“Be prepared, yes, prepare yourself, you, and all your companies who are assembled to you, and be a guard to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 38:8"},"After many days you will be visited. In the latter years you will come into the land that is brought back from the sword,\nthat is gathered out of many peoples, on the mountains of Israel, which have been a continual waste; but it is brought out of\nthe peoples, and they will dwell securely, all of them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 38:9"},"You will ascend. You will come like a storm. You will be like a cloud to cover the land, you, and all your hordes, and\nmany peoples with you.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 38:10"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “It will happen in that day that things will come into your mind, and you will devise an evil\nplan. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 38:11"},"You will say, ‘I will go up to the land of unwalled villages. I will go to those who are at rest, who dwell securely, all\nof them dwelling without walls, and having neither bars nor gates,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 38:12"},"to take the plunder and to take prey; to turn your hand against the waste places that are inhabited, and against the\npeople who are gathered out of the nations, who have gotten livestock and goods, who dwell in the middle of the earth.’\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 38:13"},"Sheba, and Dedan, and the merchants of Tarshish, with all the young lions of it, will ask you, ‘Have you come to take the\nplunder? Have you assembled your company to take the prey, to carry away silver and gold, to take away livestock and goods, to\ntake great plunder?’”’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 38:14"},"“Therefore, son of man, prophesy, and tell Gog, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “In that day when my people Israel dwells securely,\nwill you not know it? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 38:15"},"You will come from your place out of the uttermost parts of the north, you, and many peoples with you, all of them riding\non horses, a great company and a mighty army. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 38:16"},"You will come up against my people Israel, as a cloud to cover the land. It will happen in the latter days, that I will\nbring you against my land, that the nations may know me, when I am sanctified in you, Gog, before their eyes.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 38:17"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Are you he of whom I spoke in old time by my servants the prophets of Israel, who prophesied in\nthose days for years that I would bring you against them? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 38:18"},"It will happen in that day, when Gog comes against the land of Israel,” says the Lord ALLAH, “that my wrath will come up\ninto my nostrils. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 38:19"},"For in my jealousy and in the fire of my wrath I have spoken. Surely in that day there will be a great shaking in the\nland of Israel; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 38:20"},"so that the fish of the sea, the birds of the sky, the animals of the field, all creeping things who creep on the earth,\nand all the men who are on the surface of the earth will shake at my presence. Then the mountains will be thrown down, the\nsteep places will fall, and every wall will fall to the ground. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 38:21"},"I will call for a sword against him to all my mountains,” says the Lord ALLAH. “Every man’s sword will be against his\nbrother. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 38:22"},"I will enter into judgement with him with pestilence and with blood. I will rain on him, and on his hordes, and on the\nmany peoples who are with him, an overflowing shower, with great hailstones, fire, and sulphur.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 38:23"},"I will magnify myself, and sanctify myself, and I will make myself known in the eyes of many nations. Then they will know\nthat I am the LORD.”’ \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"39","sid":"EZK 39"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 39:1"},"“You, son of man, prophesy against Gog, and say, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Behold, I am against you, Gog, prince of Rosh,\nMeshech, and Tubal. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 39:2"},"I will turn you around, and will lead you on, and will cause you to come up from the uttermost parts of the north; and I\nwill bring you onto the mountains of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 39:3"},"I will strike your bow out of your left hand, and will cause your arrows to fall out of your right hand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 39:4"},"You will fall on the mountains of Israel, you, and all your hordes, and the peoples who are with you. I will give you to\nthe ravenous birds of every sort, and to the animals of the field to be devoured.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 39:5"},"You will fall on the open field; for I have spoken it,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 39:6"},"“I will send a fire on Magog, and on those who dwell securely in the islands. Then they will know that I am the LORD.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 39:7"},"“‘“I will make my holy name known amongst my people Israel. I won’t allow my holy name to be profaned any more. Then the\nnations will know that I am the LORD, the Holy One in Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 39:8"},"Behold, it comes, and it will be done,” says the Lord ALLAH. “This is the day about which I have spoken.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 39:9"},"“‘“Those who dwell in the cities of Israel will go out, and will make fires of the weapons and burn them, both the shields\nand the bucklers, the bows and the arrows, and the war clubs and the spears, and they will make fires with them for seven\nyears; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 39:10"},"so that they will take no wood out of the field, and not cut down any out of the forests; for they will make fires with\nthe weapons. They will plunder those who plundered them, and rob those who robbed them,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 39:11"},"“‘“It will happen in that day, that I will give to Gog a place for burial in Israel, the valley of those who pass through\non the east of the sea; and it will stop those who pass through. They will bury Gog and all his multitude there; and they will\ncall it ‘The valley of Hamon Gog’. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 39:12"},"“‘“The house of Israel will be burying them for seven months, that they may cleanse the land.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 39:13"},"Yes, all the people of the land will bury them; and they will become famous in the day that I will be glorified,” says\nthe Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 39:14"},"“‘“They will set apart men of continual employment, who will pass through the land. Those who pass through will go with\nthose who bury those who remain on the surface of the land, to cleanse it. After the end of seven months they will search.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 39:15"},"Those who pass through the land will pass through; and when anyone sees a man’s bone, then he will set up a sign by it,\nuntil the undertakers have buried it in the valley of Hamon Gog.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 39:16"},"Hamonah will also be the name of a city. Thus they will cleanse the land.”’\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 39:17"},"“You, son of man, the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Speak to the birds of every sort, and to every animal of the field, “Assemble\nyourselves, and come; gather yourselves on every side to my sacrifice that I sacrifice for you, even a great sacrifice on the\nmountains of Israel, that you may eat meat and drink blood. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 39:18"},"You shall eat the flesh of the mighty, and drink the blood of the princes of the earth, of rams, of lambs, and of goats,\nof bulls, all of them fatlings of Bashan. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 39:19"},"You shall eat fat until you are full, and drink blood until you are drunk, of my sacrifice which I have sacrificed for\nyou. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 39:20"},"You shall be filled at my table with horses and chariots, with mighty men, and with all men of war,” says the Lord\nALLAH.’ \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 39:21"},"“I will set my glory amongst the nations. Then all the nations will see my judgement that I have executed, and my hand\nthat I have laid on them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 39:22"},"So the house of Israel will know that I am the LORD their Allah, from that day and forward.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 39:23"},"The nations will know that the house of Israel went into captivity for their iniquity; because they trespassed against\nme, and I hid my face from them; so I gave them into the hand of their adversaries, and they all fell by the sword.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 39:24"},"I did to them according to their uncleanness and according to their transgressions. I hid my face from them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 39:25"},"“Therefore the Lord ALLAH says: ‘Now I will reverse the captivity of Yaqub, and have mercy on the whole house of Israel.\nI will be jealous for my holy name. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 39:26"},"They will bear their shame, and all their trespasses by which they have trespassed against me, when they dwell securely\nin their land, and no one will make them afraid, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 39:27"},"when I have brought them back from the peoples, and gathered them out of their enemies’ lands, and am sanctified in them\nin the sight of many nations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 39:28"},"They will know that I am the LORD their Allah, in that I caused them to go into captivity amongst the nations, and have\ngathered them to their own land. Then I will leave none of them captive any more.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 39:29"},"I won’t hide my face from them any more; for I have poured out my Spirit on the house of Israel,’ says the Lord ALLAH.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"40","sid":"EZK 40"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 40:1"},"In the twenty-fifth year of our captivity, in the beginning of the year, in the tenth day of the month, in the fourteenth\nyear after that the city was struck, in the same day, the LORD’s hand was on me, and he brought me there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 40:2"},"In the visions of Allah he brought me into the land of Israel, and set me down on a very high mountain, on which was\nsomething like the frame of a city to the south. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 40:3"},"He brought me there; and, behold, there was a man, whose appearance was like the appearance of bronze, with a line of flax\nin his hand, and a measuring reed; and he stood in the gate. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 40:4"},"The man said to me, “Son of man, see with your eyes, and hear with your ears, and set your heart on all that I will show\nyou; for you have been brought here so that I may show them to you. Declare all that you see to the house of Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 40:5"},"Behold, there was a wall on the outside of the house all around, and in the man’s hand a measuring reed six\ncubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["40:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres. Thus, a 6-cubit measuring reed would have been about 3 yards or about 2.74 metres\nlong."]}],"caller":"+"}," long, of a cubit and a hand width each. So he measured the thickness of the building, one reed; and the height, one\nreed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 40:6"},"Then he came to the gate which looks towards the east, and went up its steps. He measured the threshold of the gate, one\nreed wide; and the other threshold, one reed wide. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 40:7"},"Every lodge was one reed long and one reed wide. Between the lodges was five cubits. The threshold of the gate by the\nporch of the gate towards the house was one reed. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 40:8"},"He measured also the porch of the gate towards the house, one reed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 40:9"},"Then he measured the porch of the gate, eight cubits; and its posts, two cubits; and the porch of the gate was towards the\nhouse. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 40:10"},"The lodges of the gate eastward were three on this side, and three on that side. The three of them were of one measure.\nThe posts had one measure on this side and on that side. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 40:11"},"He measured the width of the opening of the gate, ten cubits; and the length of the gate, thirteen cubits;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 40:12"},"and a border before the lodges, one cubit on this side, and a border, one cubit on that side; and the lodges, six cubits\non this side, and six cubits on that side. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 40:13"},"He measured the gate from the roof of the one lodge to the roof of the other, a width of twenty-five cubits, door against\ndoor. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 40:14"},"He also made posts, sixty cubits; and the court reached to the posts, around the gate.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 40:15"},"From the forefront of the gate at the entrance to the forefront of the inner porch of the gate were fifty cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 40:16"},"There were closed windows to the lodges, and to their posts within the gate all around, and likewise to the arches.\nWindows were around inward. Palm trees were on each post. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 40:17"},"Then he brought me into the outer court. Behold, there were rooms and a pavement made for the court all around. Thirty\nrooms were on the pavement. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 40:18"},"The pavement was by the side of the gates, corresponding to the length of the gates, even the lower pavement.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 40:19"},"Then he measured the width from the forefront of the lower gate to the forefront of the inner court outside, one hundred\ncubits, both on the east and on the north. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 40:20"},"He measured the length and width of the gate of the outer court which faces towards the north.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 40:21"},"The lodges of it were three on this side and three on that side. Its posts and its arches were the same as the measure of\nthe first gate: its length was fifty cubits, and the width twenty-five cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 40:22"},"Its windows, its arches, and its palm trees were the same as the measure of the gate which faces towards the east. They\nwent up to it by seven steps. Its arches were before them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 40:23"},"There was a gate to the inner court facing the other gate, on the north and on the east. He measured one hundred cubits\nfrom gate to gate. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 40:24"},"He led me towards the south; and behold, there was a gate towards the south. He measured its posts and its arches\naccording to these measurements. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 40:25"},"There were windows in it and in its arches all around, like those windows: the length was fifty cubits, and the width\ntwenty-five cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 40:26"},"There were seven steps to go up to it, and its arches were before them. It had palm trees, one on this side, and another\non that side, on its posts. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 40:27"},"There was a gate to the inner court towards the south. He measured one hundred cubits from gate to gate towards the\nsouth. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 40:28"},"Then he brought me to the inner court by the south gate. He measured the south gate according to these measurements;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 40:29"},"with its lodges, its posts, and its arches, according to these measurements. There were windows in it and in its arches\nall around. It was fifty cubits long, and twenty-five cubits wide.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 40:30"},"There were arches all around, twenty-five cubits long, and five cubits wide.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 40:31"},"Its arches were towards the outer court. Palm trees were on its posts. The ascent to it had eight steps.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 40:32"},"He brought me into the inner court towards the east. He measured the gate according to these measurements;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 40:33"},"with its lodges, its posts, and its arches, according to these measurements. There were windows in it and in its arches\nall around. It was fifty cubits long, and twenty-five cubits wide.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 40:34"},"Its arches were towards the outer court. Palm trees were on its posts on this side and on that side. The ascent to it had\neight steps. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 40:35"},"He brought me to the north gate, and he measured it according to these measurements;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"36","sid":"EZK 40:36"},"its lodges, its posts, and its arches. There were windows in it all around. The length was fifty cubits and the width\ntwenty-five cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"37","sid":"EZK 40:37"},"Its posts were towards the outer court. Palm trees were on its posts on this side and on that side. The ascent to it had\neight steps. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"38","sid":"EZK 40:38"},"A room with its door was by the posts at the gates. They washed the burnt offering there.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"39","sid":"EZK 40:39"},"In the porch of the gate were two tables on this side, and two tables on that side, on which to kill the burnt offering,\nthe sin offering, and the trespass offering. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"40","sid":"EZK 40:40"},"On the one side outside, as one goes up to the entry of the gate towards the north, were two tables; and on the other\nside, which belonged to the porch of the gate, were two tables. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"41","sid":"EZK 40:41"},"Four tables were on this side, and four tables on that side, by the side of the gate: eight tables, on which they killed\nthe sacrifices. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"42","sid":"EZK 40:42"},"There were four tables for the burnt offering, of cut stone, a cubit and a half long, and a cubit and a half wide, and\none cubit high. They laid the instruments with which they killed the burnt offering and the sacrifice on them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"43","sid":"EZK 40:43"},"The hooks, a hand width long, were fastened within all around. The meat of the offering was on the tables.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"44","sid":"EZK 40:44"},"Outside of the inner gate were rooms for the singers in the inner court, which was at the side of the north gate. They\nfaced towards the south. One at the side of the east gate faced towards the north.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"45","sid":"EZK 40:45"},"He said to me, “This room, which faces towards the south, is for the priests, the keepers of the duty of the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"46","sid":"EZK 40:46"},"The room which faces towards the north is for the priests, the keepers of the duty of the altar. These are the sons of\nZadok, who from amongst the sons of Levi come near to the LORD to minister to him.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"47","sid":"EZK 40:47"},"He measured the court, one hundred cubits long, and a hundred cubits wide, square. The altar was before the house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"48","sid":"EZK 40:48"},"Then he brought me to the porch of the house, and measured each post of the porch, five cubits on this side, and five\ncubits on that side. The width of the gate was three cubits on this side and three cubits on that side.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"49","sid":"EZK 40:49"},"The length of the porch was twenty cubits, and the width eleven cubits; even by the steps by which they went up to it.\nThere were pillars by the posts, one on this side, and another on that side.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"41","sid":"EZK 41"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 41:1"},"He brought me to the temple, and measured the posts, six cubits wide on the one side, and six cubits wide on the other\nside, which was the width of the tent. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 41:2"},"The width of the entrance was ten cubits;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["41:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the\nelbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," and the sides of the entrance were five cubits on the one side,\nand five cubits on the other side. He measured its length, forty cubits, and the width, twenty cubits.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 41:3"},"Then he went inward and measured each post of the entrance, two cubits; and the entrance, six cubits; and the width of the\nentrance, seven cubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 41:4"},"He measured its length, twenty cubits, and the width, twenty cubits, before the temple. He said to me, “This is the most\nholy place.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 41:5"},"Then he measured the wall of the house, six cubits; and the width of every side room, four cubits, all around the house on\nevery side. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 41:6"},"The side rooms were in three storeys, one over another, and thirty in order. They entered into the wall which belonged to\nthe house for the side rooms all around, that they might be supported, and not penetrate the wall of the house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 41:7"},"The side rooms were wider on the higher levels, because the walls were narrower at the higher levels. Therefore the width\nof the house increased upward; and so one went up from the lowest level to the highest through the middle level.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 41:8"},"I saw also that the house had a raised base all around. The foundations of the side rooms were a full reed of six great\ncubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 41:9"},"The thickness of the wall, which was for the side rooms, on the outside, was five cubits. That which was left was the\nplace of the side rooms that belonged to the house. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 41:10"},"Between the rooms was a width of twenty cubits around the house on every side.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 41:11"},"The doors of the side rooms were towards an open area that was left, one door towards the north, and another door towards\nthe south. The width of the open area was five cubits all around.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 41:12"},"The building that was before the separate place at the side towards the west was seventy cubits wide; and the wall of the\nbuilding was five cubits thick all around, and its length ninety cubits.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 41:13"},"So he measured the house, one hundred cubits long; and the separate place, and the building, with its walls, one hundred\ncubits long; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 41:14"},"also the width of the face of the house, and of the separate place towards the east, one hundred cubits.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 41:15"},"He measured the length of the building before the separate place which was at its back, and its galleries on the one side\nand on the other side, one hundred cubits from the inner temple, and the porches of the court\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 41:16"},"the thresholds, and the closed windows, and the galleries around on their three storeys, opposite the threshold, with\nwood ceilings all around, and from the ground up to the windows, (now the windows were covered),\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 41:17"},"to the space above the door, even to the inner house, and outside, and by all the wall all around inside and outside, by\nmeasure. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 41:18"},"It was made with cherubim and palm trees. A palm tree was between cherub and cherub, and every cherub had two faces;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 41:19"},"so that there was the face of a man towards the palm tree on the one side, and the face of a young lion towards the palm\ntree on the other side. It was made like this through all the house all around.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 41:20"},"Cherubim and palm trees were made from the ground to above the door. The wall of the temple was like this.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 41:21"},"As for the temple, the door posts were squared. As for the face of the sanctuary, its appearance was as the appearance of\nthe temple. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 41:22"},"The altar was of wood, three cubits high, and its length two cubits. Its corners, its length, and its walls were of wood.\nHe said to me, “This is the table that is before the LORD.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 41:23"},"The temple and the sanctuary had two doors. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 41:24"},"The doors had two leaves each, two turning leaves: two for the one door, and two leaves for the other.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 41:25"},"There were made on them, on the doors of the temple, cherubim and palm trees, like those made on the walls. There was a\nthreshold of wood on the face of the porch outside. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 41:26"},"There were closed windows and palm trees on the one side and on the other side, on the sides of the porch. This is how\nthe side rooms of the house and the thresholds were arranged. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"42","sid":"EZK 42"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 42:1"},"Then he brought me out into the outer court, the way towards the north. Then he brought me into the room that was opposite\nthe separate place, and which was opposite the building towards the north.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 42:2"},"Before the length of one hundred cubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["42:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the\nelbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," was the north door, and the width was fifty cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 42:3"},"Opposite the twenty cubits which belonged to the inner court, and opposite the pavement which belonged to the outer court,\nwas gallery against gallery in the third floor. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 42:4"},"Before the rooms was a walk of ten cubits’ width inward, a way of one cubit; and their doors were towards the north.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 42:5"},"Now the upper rooms were shorter; for the galleries took away from these, more than from the lower and the middle, in the\nbuilding. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 42:6"},"For they were in three storeys, and they didn’t have pillars as the pillars of the courts. Therefore the uppermost was set\nback more than the lowest and the middle from the ground. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 42:7"},"The wall that was outside by the side of the rooms, towards the outer court before the rooms, its length was fifty cubits.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 42:8"},"For the length of the rooms that were in the outer court was fifty cubits. Behold, before the temple were one hundred\ncubits. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 42:9"},"From under these rooms was the entry on the east side, as one goes into them from the outer court.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 42:10"},"In the thickness of the wall of the court towards the east, before the separate place, and before the building, there\nwere rooms. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 42:11"},"The way before them was like the appearance of the rooms which were towards the north; according to their length so was\ntheir width: and all their exits were both according to their fashions, and according to their doors.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 42:12"},"According to the doors of the rooms that were towards the south was a door at the head of the way, even the way directly\nbefore the wall towards the east, as one enters into them. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 42:13"},"Then he said to me, “The north rooms and the south rooms, which are before the separate place, are the holy rooms, where\nthe priests who are near to the LORD shall eat the most holy things. There they shall lay the most holy things, with the meal\noffering, the sin offering, and the trespass offering; for the place is holy.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 42:14"},"When the priests enter in, then they shall not go out of the holy place into the outer court, but they shall lay their\ngarments in which they minister there; for they are holy. Then they shall put on other garments, and shall approach that which\nis for the people.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 42:15"},"Now when he had finished measuring the inner house, he brought me out by the way of the gate which faces towards the\neast, and measured it all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 42:16"},"He measured on the east side with the measuring reed five hundred reeds, with the measuring reed all around.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 42:17"},"He measured on the north side five hundred reeds with the measuring reed all around.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 42:18"},"He measured on the south side five hundred reeds with the measuring reed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 42:19"},"He turned about to the west side, and measured five hundred reeds with the measuring reed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 42:20"},"He measured it on the four sides. It had a wall around it, the length five hundred, and the width five hundred, to make a\nseparation between that which was holy and that which was common.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"43","sid":"EZK 43"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 43:1"},"Afterward he brought me to the gate, even the gate that looks towards the east.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 43:2"},"Behold, the glory of Allah of Israel came from the way of the east. His voice was like the sound of many waters; and the\nearth was illuminated with his glory. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 43:3"},"It was according to the appearance of the vision which I saw, even according to the vision that I saw when I came to\ndestroy the city; and the visions were like the vision that I saw by the river Chebar; and I fell on my face.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 43:4"},"The LORD’s glory came into the house by the way of the gate which faces towards the east.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 43:5"},"The Spirit took me up, and brought me into the inner court; and behold, the LORD’s glory filled the house.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 43:6"},"I heard one speaking to me out of the house; and a man stood by me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 43:7"},"He said to me, “Son of man, this is the place of my throne, and the place of the soles of my feet, where I will dwell\namongst the children of Israel forever. The house of Israel will no more defile my holy name, neither they, nor their kings, by\ntheir prostitution, and by the dead bodies of their kings in their high places;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 43:8"},"in their setting of their threshold by my threshold, and their door post beside my door post. There was a wall between me\nand them; and they have defiled my holy name by their abominations which they have committed. Therefore I have consumed them in\nmy anger. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 43:9"},"Now let them put away their prostitution, and the dead bodies of their kings, far from me. Then I will dwell amongst them\nforever. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 43:10"},"“You, son of man, show the house to the house of Israel, that they may be ashamed of their iniquities; and let them\nmeasure the pattern. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 43:11"},"If they are ashamed of all that they have done, make known to them the form of the house, and its fashion, and its exits,\nand its entrances, and all its forms, and all its ordinances, and all its forms, and all its laws; and write it in their sight;\nthat they may keep the whole form of it, and all its ordinances, and do them.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 43:12"},"“This is the law of the house. On the top of the mountain the whole limit around it shall be most holy. Behold, this is\nthe law of the house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 43:13"},"“These are the measurements of the altar by cubits (the cubit",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":[" \n",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["43:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18 inches or 46\ncentimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," is a cubit and a hand width): the bottom shall be a cubit, and the width a cubit, and its border around its\nedge a span;",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["43:13 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A span is the length from the tip of a man’s thumb to the tip of his little finger when his\nhand is stretched out (about half a cubit, or 9 inches, or 22.8 cm.)"]}],"caller":"+"}," and this shall be the base of the altar.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 43:14"},"From the bottom on the ground to the lower ledge shall be two cubits, and the width one cubit; and from the lesser ledge\nto the greater ledge shall be four cubits, and the width a cubit.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 43:15"},"The upper altar shall be four cubits; and from the altar hearth and upward there shall be four horns.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 43:16"},"The altar hearth shall be twelve cubits long by twelve wide, square in its four sides.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 43:17"},"The ledge shall be fourteen cubits long by fourteen wide in its four sides; and the border about it shall be half a\ncubit; and its bottom shall be a cubit around; and its steps shall look towards the east.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 43:18"},"He said to me, “Son of man, the Lord ALLAH says: ‘These are the ordinances of the altar in the day when they make it, to\noffer burnt offerings on it, and to sprinkle blood on it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 43:19"},"You shall give to the Levitical priests who are of the offspring of Zadok, who are near to me, to minister to me,’ says\nthe Lord ALLAH, ‘a young bull for a sin offering. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 43:20"},"You shall take of its blood, and put it on its four horns, and on the four corners of the ledge, and on the border all\naround. You shall cleanse it and make atonement for it that way.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 43:21"},"You shall also take the bull of the sin offering, and it shall be burnt in the appointed place of the house, outside of\nthe sanctuary. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 43:22"},"“On the second day you shall offer a male goat without defect for a sin offering; and they shall cleanse the altar, as\nthey cleansed it with the bull. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 43:23"},"When you have finished cleansing it, you shall offer a young bull without defect, and a ram out of the flock without\ndefect. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 43:24"},"You shall bring them near to the LORD, and the priests shall cast salt on them, and they shall offer them up for a burnt\noffering to the LORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 43:25"},"“Seven days you shall prepare every day a goat for a sin offering. They shall also prepare a young bull, and a ram out of\nthe flock, without defect. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 43:26"},"Seven days shall they make atonement for the altar and purify it. So shall they consecrate it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 43:27"},"When they have accomplished the days, it shall be that on the eighth day, and forward, the priests shall make your burnt\nofferings on the altar, and your peace offerings. Then I will accept you,’ says the Lord ALLAH.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"44","sid":"EZK 44"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 44:1"},"Then he brought me back by the way of the outer gate of the sanctuary, which looks towards the east; and it was shut.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 44:2"},"The LORD said to me, “This gate shall be shut. It shall not be opened, no man shall enter in by it; for the LORD, Allah of\nIsrael, has entered in by it. Therefore it shall be shut. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 44:3"},"As for the prince, he shall sit in it as prince to eat bread before the LORD. He shall enter by the way of the porch of\nthe gate, and shall go out the same way.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 44:4"},"Then he brought me by the way of the north gate before the house; and I looked, and behold, the LORD’s glory filled the\nLORD’s house; so I fell on my face. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 44:5"},"The LORD said to me, “Son of man, mark well, and see with your eyes, and hear with your ears all that I tell you\nconcerning all the ordinances of the LORD’s house, and all its laws; and mark well the entrance of the house, with every exit\nof the sanctuary. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 44:6"},"You shall tell the rebellious, even the house of Israel, ‘The Lord ALLAH says: “You house of Israel, let that be enough of\nall your abominations, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 44:7"},"in that you have brought in foreigners, uncircumcised in heart and uncircumcised in flesh, to be in my sanctuary, to\nprofane it, even my house, when you offer my bread, the fat and the blood, and they have broken my covenant, to add to all your\nabominations. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 44:8"},"You have not performed the duty of my holy things; but you have set performers of my duty in my sanctuary for yourselves.”\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 44:9"},"The Lord ALLAH says, “No foreigner, uncircumcised in heart and uncircumcised in flesh, shall enter into my sanctuary, of\nany foreigners who are amongst the children of Israel. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 44:10"},"“‘“But the Levites who went far from me, when Israel went astray, who went astray from me after their idols, they will\nbear their iniquity. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 44:11"},"Yet they shall be ministers in my sanctuary, having oversight at the gates of the house, and ministering in the house.\nThey shall kill the burnt offering and the sacrifice for the people, and they shall stand before them to minister to them.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 44:12"},"Because they ministered to them before their idols, and became a stumbling block of iniquity to the house of Israel.\nTherefore I have lifted up my hand against them,” says the Lord ALLAH, “and they will bear their iniquity.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 44:13"},"They shall not come near to me, to execute the office of priest to me, nor to come near to any of my holy things, to the\nthings that are most holy; but they will bear their shame, and their abominations which they have committed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 44:14"},"Yet I will make them performers of the duty of the house, for all its service, and for all that will be done therein.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 44:15"},"“‘“But the Levitical priests, the sons of Zadok, who performed the duty of my sanctuary when the children of Israel went\nastray from me, shall come near to me to minister to me. They shall stand before me to offer to me the fat and the blood,” says\nthe Lord ALLAH. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 44:16"},"“They shall enter into my sanctuary, and they shall come near to my table, to minister to me, and they shall keep my\ninstruction. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 44:17"},"“‘“It will be that, when they enter in at the gates of the inner court, they shall be clothed with linen garments. No\nwool shall come on them while they minister in the gates of the inner court, and within.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 44:18"},"They shall have linen turbans on their heads, and shall have linen trousers on their waists. They shall not clothe\nthemselves with anything that makes them sweat. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 44:19"},"When they go out into the outer court, even into the outer court to the people, they shall put off their garments in\nwhich they minister, and lay them in the holy rooms. They shall put on other garments, that they not sanctify the people with\ntheir garments. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 44:20"},"“‘“They shall not shave their heads, or allow their locks to grow long. They shall only cut off the hair of their heads.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 44:21"},"None of the priests shall drink wine when they enter into the inner court.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 44:22"},"They shall not take for their wives a widow, or her who is put away; but they shall take virgins of the offspring of the\nhouse of Israel, or a widow who is the widow of a priest. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 44:23"},"They shall teach my people the difference between the holy and the common, and cause them to discern between the unclean\nand the clean. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 44:24"},"“‘“In a controversy they shall stand to judge. They shall judge it according to my ordinances. They shall keep my laws\nand my statutes in all my appointed feasts. They shall make my Sabbaths holy.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 44:25"},"“‘“They shall go in to no dead person to defile themselves; but for father, or for mother, or for son, or for daughter,\nfor brother, or for sister who has had no husband, they may defile themselves.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 44:26"},"After he is cleansed, they shall reckon to him seven days.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 44:27"},"In the day that he goes into the sanctuary, into the inner court, to minister in the sanctuary, he shall offer his sin\noffering,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 44:28"},"“‘They shall have an inheritance. I am their inheritance; and you shall give them no possession in Israel. I am their\npossession. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 44:29"},"They shall eat the meal offering, and the sin offering, and the trespass offering; and every devoted thing in Israel\nshall be theirs. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 44:30"},"The first of all the first fruits of every thing, and every offering of everything, of all your offerings, shall be for\nthe priest. You shall also give to the priests the first of your dough, to cause a blessing to rest on your house.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 44:31"},"The priests shall not eat of anything that dies of itself, or is torn, whether it is bird or animal.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"45","sid":"EZK 45"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 45:1"},"“‘“Moreover, when you divide by lot the land for inheritance, you shall offer an offering to the LORD, a holy portion of\nthe land. The length shall be the length of twenty-five thousand reeds, and the width shall be ten thousand. It shall be holy\nin all its border all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 45:2"},"Of this there shall be a five hundred by five hundred square for the holy place; and fifty\ncubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," for its pasture lands all around. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 45:3"},"Of this measure you shall measure a length of twenty-five thousand, and a width of ten thousand. In it shall be the\nsanctuary, which is most holy. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 45:4"},"It is a holy portion of the land; it shall be for the priests, the ministers of the sanctuary, who come near to minister\nto the LORD. It shall be a place for their houses and a holy place for the sanctuary.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 45:5"},"Twenty-five thousand in length, and ten thousand in width, shall be for the Levites, the ministers of the house, as a\npossession for themselves, for twenty rooms. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 45:6"},"“‘“You shall appoint the possession of the city five thousand wide, and twenty-five thousand long, side by side with the\noffering of the holy portion: it shall be for the whole house of Israel.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 45:7"},"“‘“What is for the prince shall be on the one side and on the other side of the holy offering and of the possession of the\ncity, in front of the holy offering and in front of the possession of the city, on the west side westward, and on the east side\neastward; and in length answerable to one of the portions, from the west border to the east border.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 45:8"},"In the land it shall be to him for a possession in Israel. My princes shall no more oppress my people; but they shall give\nthe land to the house of Israel according to their tribes.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 45:9"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “Let it suffice you, princes of Israel: remove violence and plunder, and execute justice and\nrighteousness; dispossessing my people,” says the Lord ALLAH. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 45:10"},"“You shall have just balances, a just ephah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:10\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a bushel"]}],"caller":"+"}," and a just bath.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 45:11"},"The ephah and the bath shall be of one measure, that the bath may contain one tenth of a\nhomer,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 homer is about 220 litres or 6 bushels"]}],"caller":"+"}," and the ephah one tenth of a homer. Its measure shall be\nthe same as the homer. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 45:12"},"The shekel",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35\nounces."]}],"caller":"+"}," shall be twenty gerahs.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["a gerah is about 0.5 grams or about 7.7\ngrains"]}],"caller":"+"}," Twenty shekels plus twenty-five shekels plus fifteen shekels shall be your\nmina.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:12 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A mina is about 600 grams or 1.3 U. S. pounds."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 45:13"},"“‘“This is the offering that you shall offer: the sixth part of an ephah from a homer of wheat; and you shall give the\nsixth part of an ephah from a homer of barley; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 45:14"},"and the set portion of oil, of the bath of oil, one tenth of a bath out of the cor, which is ten baths, even a homer;\n(for ten baths are a homer;)",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 cor is the same as 1 homer in volume, and is about 211 litres, 55.9 gallons,\nor 6 bushels. 1 bath is about 21.1 litres, 5.59 gallons, or 2.4 pecks."]}],"caller":"+"},"\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 45:15"},"and one lamb of the flock, out of two hundred, from the well-watered pastures of Israel—for a meal offering, and for a\nburnt offering, and for peace offerings, to make atonement for them,” says the Lord ALLAH.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 45:16"},"“All the people of the land shall give to this offering for the prince in Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 45:17"},"It shall be the prince’s part to give the burnt offerings, the meal offerings, and the drink offerings, in the feasts,\nand on the new moons, and on the Sabbaths, in all the appointed feasts of the house of Israel. He shall prepare the sin\noffering, the meal offering, the burnt offering, and the peace offerings, to make atonement for the house of Israel.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 45:18"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “In the first month, in the first day of the month, you shall take a young bull without defect;\nand you shall cleanse the sanctuary. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 45:19"},"The priest shall take of the blood of the sin offering, and put it on the door posts of the house, and on the four\ncorners of the ledge of the altar, and on the posts of the gate of the inner court.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 45:20"},"So you shall do on the seventh day of the month for everyone who errs, and for him who is simple. So you shall make\natonement for the house. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 45:21"},"“‘“In the first month, in the fourteenth day of the month, you shall have the Passover, a feast of seven days; unleavened\nbread shall be eaten. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 45:22"},"On that day the prince shall prepare for himself and for all the people of the land a bull for a sin offering.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 45:23"},"The seven days of the feast he shall prepare a burnt offering to the LORD, seven bulls and seven rams without defect\ndaily the seven days; and a male goat daily for a sin offering. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 45:24"},"He shall prepare a meal offering, an ephah",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:24 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}],"caller":"+"}," for a bull, and an ephah for a ram, and a hin",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["45:24\n"]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A hin is about 6.5 litres or 1.7 gallons."]}],"caller":"+"}," of oil to an ephah.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 45:25"},"“‘“In the seventh month, in the fifteenth day of the month, in the feast, he shall do like that for seven days; according\nto the sin offering, according to the burnt offering, and according to the meal offering, and according to the oil.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"46","sid":"EZK 46"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 46:1"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “The gate of the inner court that looks towards the east shall be shut the six working days; but on\nthe Sabbath day it shall be opened, and on the day of the new moon it shall be opened.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 46:2"},"The prince shall enter by the way of the porch of the gate outside, and shall stand by the post of the gate; and the\npriests shall prepare his burnt offering and his peace offerings, and he shall worship at the threshold of the gate. Then he\nshall go out; but the gate shall not be shut until the evening. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 46:3"},"The people of the land shall worship at the door of that gate before the LORD on the Sabbaths and on the new moons.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 46:4"},"The burnt offering that the prince shall offer to the LORD shall be on the Sabbath day six lambs without defect and a ram\nwithout defect; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 46:5"},"and the meal offering shall be an ephah for the ram, and the meal offering for the lambs as he is able to give, and a\nhin",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A hin is about 6.5 litres or 1.7 gallons."]}],"caller":"+"}," of oil to an\nephah.",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:5 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 46:6"},"On the day of the new moon it shall be a young bull without defect, and six lambs, and a ram. They shall be without\ndefect. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 46:7"},"He shall prepare a meal offering, an ephah for the bull, and an ephah for the ram, and for the lambs according as he is\nable, and a hin of oil to an ephah. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 46:8"},"When the prince enters, he shall go in by the way of the porch of the gate, and he shall go out by its way.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 46:9"},"“‘“But when the people of the land come before the LORD in the appointed feasts, he who enters by the way of the north\ngate to worship shall go out by the way of the south gate; and he who enters by the way of the south gate shall go out by the\nway of the north gate. He shall not return by the way of the gate by which he came in, but shall go out straight before him.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 46:10"},"The prince shall go in with them when they go in. When they go out, he shall go out.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 46:11"},"“‘“In the feasts and in the solemnities the meal offering shall be an ephah\n",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:11 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}],"caller":"+"}," for a bull, and an ephah for a ram, and for the lambs as he is able to give, and a hin of oil to an ephah.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 46:12"},"When the prince prepares a free will offering, a burnt offering or peace offerings as a free will offering to the LORD,\none shall open for him the gate that looks towards the east; and he shall prepare his burnt offering and his peace offerings,\nas he does on the Sabbath day. Then he shall go out; and after his going out one shall shut the gate.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 46:13"},"“‘“You shall prepare a lamb a year old without defect for a burnt offering to the LORD daily. Morning by morning you\nshall prepare it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 46:14"},"You shall prepare a meal offering with it morning by morning, the sixth part of an\nephah,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:14 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["1 ephah is about 22 litres or about 2/3 of a\nbushel"]}],"caller":"+"}," and the third part of a hin of oil, to moisten the fine flour; a meal offering to the LORD continually by a perpetual\nordinance. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 46:15"},"Thus they shall prepare the lamb, the meal offering, and the oil, morning by morning, for a continual burnt offering.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 46:16"},"“‘The Lord ALLAH says: “If the prince gives a gift to any of his sons, it is his inheritance. It shall belong to his\nsons. It is their possession by inheritance. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 46:17"},"But if he gives of his inheritance a gift to one of his servants, it shall be his to the year of liberty; then it shall\nreturn to the prince; but as for his inheritance, it shall be for his sons.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 46:18"},"Moreover the prince shall not take of the people’s inheritance, to thrust them out of their possession. He shall give\ninheritance to his sons out of his own possession, that my people not each be scattered from his possession.”’”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 46:19"},"Then he brought me through the entry, which was at the side of the gate, into the holy rooms for the priests, which\nlooked towards the north. Behold, there was a place on the back part westward.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 46:20"},"He said to me, “This is the place where the priests shall boil the trespass offering and the sin offering, and where they\nshall bake the meal offering; that they not bring them out into the outer court, to sanctify the people.”\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 46:21"},"Then he brought me out into the outer court, and caused me to pass by the four corners of the court; and behold, in every\ncorner of the court there was a court. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 46:22"},"In the four corners of the court there were courts enclosed, forty\ncubits",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["46:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," long and thirty wide. These four in the corners were the same size.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 46:23"},"There was a wall around in them, around the four, and boiling places were made under the walls all around.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 46:24"},"Then he said to me, “These are the boiling houses, where the ministers of the house shall boil the sacrifice of the\npeople.” \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"47","sid":"EZK 47"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 47:1"},"He brought me back to the door of the house; and behold, waters flowed out from under the threshold of the house eastward,\nfor the front of the house faced towards the east. The waters came down from underneath, from the right side of the house, on\nthe south of the altar. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 47:2"},"Then he brought me out by the way of the gate northward, and led me around by the way outside to the outer gate, by the\nway of the gate that looks towards the east. Behold, waters ran out on the right side.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 47:3"},"When the man went out eastward with the line in his hand, he measured one thousand\ncubits,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["47:3 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["A cubit is the length from the tip of the middle finger to the elbow on a man’s arm, or about 18\ninches or 46 centimetres."]}],"caller":"+"}," and he caused me to pass through the waters, waters that were to the ankles.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 47:4"},"Again he measured one thousand, and caused me to pass through the waters, waters that were to the knees. Again he measured\none thousand, and caused me to pass through waters that were to the waist.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 47:5"},"Afterward he measured one thousand; and it was a river that I could not pass through; for the waters had risen, waters to\nswim in, a river that could not be walked through. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 47:6"},"He said to me, “Son of man, have you seen?” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["Then he brought me, and caused me to return to the bank of the river.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 47:7"},"Now when I had returned, behold, on the bank of the river were very many trees on the one side and on the other.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 47:8"},"Then he said to me, “These waters flow out towards the eastern region, and will go down into the Arabah. Then they will go\ntowards the sea; and flow into the sea which will be made to flow out; and the waters will be healed.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 47:9"},"It will happen, that every living creature which swarms, in every place where the rivers come, will live. Then there will\nbe a very great multitude of fish; for these waters have come there, and the waters of the sea will be healed, and everything\nwill live wherever the river comes. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 47:10"},"It will happen, that fishermen will stand by it. From En Gedi even to En Eglaim will be a place for the spreading of\nnets. Their fish will be after their kinds, as the fish of the great sea, exceedingly many.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 47:11"},"But the miry places of it, and its marshes, will not be healed. They will be given up to salt.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 47:12"},"By the river on its bank, on this side and on that side, will grow every tree for food, whose leaf won’t wither, neither\nwill its fruit fail. It will produce new fruit every month, because its waters issue out of the sanctuary. Its fruit will be\nfor food, and its leaf for healing.” \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 47:13"},"The Lord ALLAH says: “This shall be the border, by which you shall divide the land for inheritance according to the\ntwelve tribes of Israel. Yusuf shall have two portions. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 47:14"},"You shall inherit it, one as well as another; for I swore to give it to your fathers. This land will fall to you for\ninheritance. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 47:15"},"“This shall be the border of the land: \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":["“On the north side, from the great sea, by the way of Hethlon, to the entrance of Zedad;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 47:16"},"Hamath, Berothah, Sibraim, which is between the border of Damascus and the border of Hamath; Hazer Hatticon, which is by\nthe border of Hauran. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 47:17"},"The border from the sea, shall be Hazar Enon at the border of Damascus; and on the north northward is the border of\nHamath. This is the north side. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 47:18"},"“The east side, between Hauran and Damascus and Gilead, and the land of Israel, shall be the Jordan; from the north\nborder to the east sea you shall measure. This is the east side.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 47:19"},"“The south side southward shall be from Tamar as far as the waters of Meriboth Kadesh, to the brook, to the great sea.\nThis is the south side southward. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 47:20"},"“The west side shall be the great sea, from the south border as far as opposite the entrance of Hamath. This is the west\nside. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 47:21"},"“So you shall divide this land to yourselves according to the tribes of Israel.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 47:22"},"It will happen, that you shall divide it by lot for an inheritance to you and to the aliens who live amongst you, who\nwill father children amongst you. Then they shall be to you as the native-born amongst the children of Israel. They shall have\ninheritance with you amongst the tribes of Israel. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 47:23"},"It shall happen, that in whatever tribe the stranger lives, there you shall give him his inheritance,” says the Lord\nALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"48","sid":"EZK 48"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"EZK 48:1"},"“Now these are the names of the tribes: From the north end, beside the way of Hethlon to the entrance of Hamath, Hazar\nEnan at the border of Damascus, northward beside Hamath (and they shall have their sides east and west), Dan, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"EZK 48:2"},"“By the border of Dan, from the east side to the west side, Asher, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"EZK 48:3"},"“By the border of Asher, from the east side even to the west side, Naphtali, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"EZK 48:4"},"“By the border of Naphtali, from the east side to the west side, Manasseh, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"EZK 48:5"},"“By the border of Manasseh, from the east side to the west side, Ephraim, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"EZK 48:6"},"“By the border of Ephraim, from the east side even to the west side, Reuben, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"EZK 48:7"},"“By the border of Reuben, from the east side to the west side, Judah, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"EZK 48:8"},"“By the border of Judah, from the east side to the west side, shall be the offering which you shall offer, twenty-five\nthousand reeds in width, and in length as one of the portions, from the east side to the west side: and the sanctuary shall be\nin the middle of it. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"EZK 48:9"},"“The offering that you shall offer to the LORD shall be twenty-five thousand reeds in length, and ten thousand in width.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"EZK 48:10"},"For these, even for the priests, shall be the holy offering: towards the north twenty-five thousand in length, and\ntowards the west ten thousand in width, and towards the east ten thousand in width, and towards the south twenty-five thousand\nin length: and the sanctuary of the LORD shall be in the middle of it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"EZK 48:11"},"It shall be for the priests who are sanctified of the sons of Zadok, who have kept my instruction, who didn’t go astray\nwhen the children of Israel went astray, as the Levites went astray.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"EZK 48:12"},"It shall be to them an offering from the offering of the land, a most holy thing, by the border of the Levites.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"EZK 48:13"},"“Answerable to the border of the priests, the Levites shall have twenty-five thousand in length, and ten thousand in\nwidth. All the length shall be twenty-five thousand, and the width ten thousand.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"EZK 48:14"},"They shall sell none of it, nor exchange it, nor shall the first fruits of the land be alienated; for it is holy to the\nLORD. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"EZK 48:15"},"“The five thousand that are left in the width, in front of the twenty-five thousand, shall be for common use, for the\ncity, for dwelling and for pasture lands; and the city shall be in the middle of it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"EZK 48:16"},"These shall be its measurements: the north side four thousand and five hundred, and the south side four thousand and five\nhundred, and on the east side four thousand and five hundred, and the west side four thousand and five hundred.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"EZK 48:17"},"The city shall have pasture lands: towards the north two hundred and fifty, and towards the south two hundred and fifty,\nand towards the east two hundred and fifty, and towards the west two hundred and fifty.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"EZK 48:18"},"The remainder in the length, alongside the holy offering, shall be ten thousand eastward, and ten thousand westward; and\nit shall be alongside the holy offering. Its increase shall be for food to those who labour in the city.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"EZK 48:19"},"Those who labour in the city, out of all the tribes of Israel, shall cultivate it.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"EZK 48:20"},"All the offering shall be a square of twenty-five thousand by twenty-five thousand. You shall offer it as a holy\noffering, with the possession of the city. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"EZK 48:21"},"“The remainder shall be for the prince, on the one side and on the other of the holy offering and of the possession of\nthe city; in front of the twenty-five thousand of the offering towards the east border, and westward in front of the\ntwenty-five thousand towards the west border, alongside the portions, it shall be for the prince. The holy offering and the\nsanctuary of the house shall be in the middle of it. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"EZK 48:22"},"Moreover from the possession of the Levites, and from the possession of the city, being in the middle of that which is\nthe prince’s, between the border of Judah and the border of Benjamin, shall be for the prince.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"23","sid":"EZK 48:23"},"“As for the rest of the tribes: from the east side to the west side, Benjamin, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"24","sid":"EZK 48:24"},"“By the border of Benjamin, from the east side to the west side, Simeon, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"25","sid":"EZK 48:25"},"“By the border of Simeon, from the east side to the west side, Issachar, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"26","sid":"EZK 48:26"},"“By the border of Issachar, from the east side to the west side, Zebulun, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"27","sid":"EZK 48:27"},"“By the border of Zebulun, from the east side to the west side, Gad, one portion.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"28","sid":"EZK 48:28"},"“By the border of Gad, at the south side southward, the border shall be even from Tamar to the waters of Meribath Kadesh,\nto the brook, to the great sea. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"29","sid":"EZK 48:29"},"“This is the land which you shall divide by lot to the tribes of Israel for inheritance, and these are their several\nportions, says the Lord ALLAH. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"30","sid":"EZK 48:30"},"“These are the exits of the city: On the north side four thousand and five hundred reeds by measure;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"31","sid":"EZK 48:31"},"and the gates of the city shall be named after the tribes of Israel, three gates northward: the gate of Reuben, one; the\ngate of Judah, one; the gate of Levi, one. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"32","sid":"EZK 48:32"},"“At the east side four thousand and five hundred reeds, and three gates: even the gate of Yusuf, one; the gate of\nBenjamin, one; the gate of Dan, one. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"33","sid":"EZK 48:33"},"“At the south side four thousand and five hundred reeds by measure, and three gates: the gate of Simeon, one; the gate of\nIssachar, one; the gate of Zebulun, one. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"34","sid":"EZK 48:34"},"“At the west side four thousand and five hundred reeds, with their three gates: the gate of Gad, one; the gate of Asher,\none; the gate of Naphtali, one. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"35","sid":"EZK 48:35"},"“It shall be eighteen thousand reeds around: and the name of the city from that day shall be, ‘The LORD is there.’\n"]}]}